'''Abel Makkonen Tesfaye''' ({{langx|am|አቤል መኮንን ተስፋዬ}}; born February 16, 1990), known professionally as '''the<!-- lowercase per [[MOS:THENICKNAME]] --> Weeknd''', is a Canadian singer-songwriter and actor.<!--Keep notable occupations in lead per [[MOS:ROLEBIO]].--><ref name="Fantasy2">{{Cite news|last=Eells|first=Josh|date=October 21, 2015|title=Sex, Drugs and R&B: Inside The Weeknd's Dark Twisted Fantasy|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|mode=cs2|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/sex-drugs-and-rb-inside-the-weeknds-dark-twisted-fantasy-176091/|url-status=live|url-access=limited|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615145745/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/sex-drugs-and-r-b-inside-the-weeknds-dark-twisted-fantasy-20151021|archive-date=June 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Donnelly |first1=Matt |last2=Sharf |first2=Zack |date=May 22, 2023 |title='The Idol' Scandalizes Cannes With Five-Minute Standing Ovation for Lily-Rose Depp's Masturbating Pop Star, Explicit Nudity and the Weeknd's TV Acting Debut |url=https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/the-idol-cannes-weeknd-standing-ovation-lily-rose-depp-nudity-1235621084/ |access-date=June 6, 2023 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|mode=cs2|language=en-US |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161015/https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/the-idol-cannes-weeknd-standing-ovation-lily-rose-depp-nudity-1235621084/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Recognized for his unconventional musical production, artistic reinventions, and signature [[falsetto]] register, Tesfaye is one of the most innovative and influential artists of his generation.

Tesfaye began releasing music [[anonymity|anonymous]]ly in 2009. After co-founding the record label [[XO (record label)|XO]], he released three mixtapes—''[[House of Balloons]]'', ''[[Thursday (album)|Thursday]]'', and ''[[Echoes of Silence]]''—in 2011, and gained recognition for his blend of [[contemporary R&B|contemporary]] and [[alternative R&B]], as well as the mystery surrounding his identity. He signed with [[Republic Records]] to reissue the mixtapes into the compilation album ''[[Trilogy (The Weeknd album)|Trilogy]]'' (2012), and release his debut studio album, ''[[Kiss Land]]'' (2013) the following year. After a string of collaborations and film soundtrack contributions from 2013 and 2014, Tesfaye transitioned from alternative R&B to a [[pop music|pop]] sound with his second and third studio albums, ''[[Beauty Behind the Madness]]'' (2015) and ''[[Starboy (album)|Starboy]]'' (2016), both of which debuted atop the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. The former yielded his first two US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] number-one singles, "[[Can't Feel My Face]]" and "[[The Hills (song)|The Hills]]", while ''Starboy'' spawned two more: its [[Starboy (song)|title track]] (featuring [[Daft Punk]]), and after a 2023 remix with [[Ariana Grande]], "[[Die for You (The Weeknd song)|Die for You]]".

He returned to alternative R&B for his debut [[extended play]], ''[[My Dear Melancholy]]'' (2018), which included the US top-ten single "[[Call Out My Name]]". He explored the [[dream-pop]] and [[new wave music|new wave]] genres with his fourth studio album, ''[[After Hours (The Weeknd album)|After Hours]]'' (2020), which spawned the record-setting single, "[[Blinding Lights]]", in which became the [[List of Spotify streaming records|most-streamed song of all time on Spotify]], broke records as the longest-charting song in Billboard Hot 100 history, and was named the chart's best-performing song of all time. Other chart-topping singles from the album included "[[Heartless (The Weeknd song)|Heartless]]" and "[[Save Your Tears]]" with the latter gaining renewed popularity after a remix featuring [[Ariana Grande]]. Tesfaye began exploring [[dance-pop]], leading to his fifth album, ''[[Dawn FM]]'' (2022), which included the US top-ten single, "[[Take My Breath]]". In 2023, he co-created and starred in the [[HBO]] drama series ''[[The Idol (TV series)|The Idol]]'', which was a critical failure, while its [[Music from The Idol|accompanying soundtrack]] saw commercial success.

Tesfaye has sold over 75 million records, making him one of the [[List of best-selling music artists|world's best-selling artists]]. He has earned seven [[RIAA certification|diamond-certifications]] from the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for his singles, and is the first artist to simultaneously hold the top three spots on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart. "Blinding Lights" became the [[List of Billboard Hot 100 chart achievements and milestones#Top 10 songs of all time (1958–2021)|best-performing song in the ''Billboard'' Hot 100's history]] and the longest-charting song by a solo artist in the chart's history. Tesfaye was listed by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' as one of the world's [[Time 100|most influential people]] in 2020, and was dubbed the "world's most popular artist" by ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' in 2023. An advocate for [[racial equality]] and [[food security]], he was appointed a [[World Food Programme]] [[Goodwill ambassador|Goodwill Ambassador]] in 2021. He has donated millions to causes related to racial equality, food security, and disaster relief, including substantial contributions to COVID-19 relief efforts and the Ethiopian humanitarian crisis. His [[List of awards and nominations received by the Weeknd|accolades]] include four [[Grammy Award]]s, 20 [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]], 22 [[Juno Award]]s, six [[American Music Awards]], three [[MTV Video Music Awards]], a [[Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy Award]] and nominations for an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] and a [[Primetime Emmy Awards|Primetime Emmy Award]].

== Life and career ==
===Early life===
Abel Makkonen Tesfaye{{efn|[[Naming conventions in Ethiopia and Eritrea|Ethiopians do not use surnames]] but rather their father's first name as their family name. Makkonen would traditionally be his family name and Tesfaye would be his grandfather's name.}} was born on February 16, 1990, in Toronto, Ontario, Canada.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/the-weeknd/|title=The Weeknd|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=March 11, 2024|mode=cs2|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240308080720/https://www.billboard.com/artist/the-weeknd/|archive-date=March 8, 2024|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Biggest">{{Cite news |last=Caramanica |first=Jon |author-link=Jon Caramanica |date=July 27, 2015 |title=Can The Weeknd Turn Himself into the Biggest Pop Star in the World? |work=[[The New York Times Magazine]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/magazine/can-the-weeknd-turn-himself-into-the-biggest-pop-star-in-the-world.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001215630/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/magazine/can-the-weeknd-turn-himself-into-the-biggest-pop-star-in-the-world.html?_r=0 |archive-date=October 1, 2015|mode=cs2|access-date=March 11, 2024}}</ref> The only child of Ethiopian [[Amhara people|Amhara]] immigrants Makkonen Tesfaye and Samrawit Hailu,{{Efn|Tesfaye's biological parents were never married. When Tesfaye made a donation to the [[University of Toronto]]'s Ethiopic program in November 2020, the full name of his mother was revealed as Samrawit Hailu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.utoronto.ca/news/support-weeknd-u-t-s-ethiopic-program-soars-past-500000-endowment-goal|title=With support from The Weeknd, U of T's Ethiopic program soars past $500,000 endowment goal|date=November 2, 2020|website=University of Toronto|access-date=November 3, 2020|archive-date=July 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220706210855/https://www.utoronto.ca/news/support-weeknd-u-t-s-ethiopic-program-soars-past-500000-endowment-goal|url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref>}} who separated shortly after his birth,<ref name="Mistry">{{Cite news |last=Mistry |first=Anupa |date=December 23, 2011 |title=Daily Disc: The Weeknd's 'Echoes Of Silence' |work=[[Toronto Standard]] |url=http://www.torontostandard.com/culture/daily-disc-the-weeknds-echoes-of-silence/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129110625/http://www.torontostandard.com/culture/daily-disc-the-weeknds-echoes-of-silence/ |archive-date=November 29, 2019|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref name="Fantasy3">{{Cite news |last=Eells |first=Josh |date=October 21, 2015 |title=Sex, Drugs and R&B: Inside The Weeknd's Dark Twisted Fantasy |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/sex-drugs-and-rb-inside-the-weeknds-dark-twisted-fantasy-176091/ |url-status=live |url-access=limited |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615145745/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/sex-drugs-and-r-b-inside-the-weeknds-dark-twisted-fantasy-20151021 |archive-date=June 15, 2018|mode=cs2}}</ref> he was raised in the suburb of [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]] by his mother and grandmother.<ref name="Biggest" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/the-weeknd-songs-lyrics-super-bowl-halftime-show/bbt2m5plh8q216w2yb5jficq9 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208022212/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/the-weeknd-songs-lyrics-super-bowl-halftime-show/bbt2m5plh8q216w2yb5jficq9 |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |last=Rivera |first=Joe |date=February 7, 2021 |title=Who is The Weeknd? Super Bowl 55 halftime show performer's songs, lyrics & more to know |website=[[Sporting News]]}}</ref> Tesfaye's patronymic is spelled "Makkonen" instead of the traditional Ethiopian name "[[Makonnen]]". The similarity with the [[Finland|Finnish]] surname [[Makkonen]] is pure coincidence. The spelling of Tesfaye's patronymic might be the result of a typographic error or a new form of the traditional name.<ref>{{cite web|last=Määttänen|first=Juuso|url=https://www.iltalehti.fi/viihde/a/201612162200041835|title=Kesällä Suomeen saapuvan supertähden Weekndin oikea nimi on Makkonen - ei silti yhteyttä Suomeen|website=iltalehti.fi|date=December 16, 2016|access-date=April 8, 2024|language=FI|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240408103455/https://www.iltalehti.fi/viihde/a/201612162200041835|archive-date=April 8, 2024}}</ref> Tesfaye is proficient in [[Amharic]], his native language acquired from his grandmother,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lamb |first=Karas |date=September 16, 2013 |title=The Weeknd Reveals The Origin Of His Name + More |url=https://www.okayplayer.com/news/the-weeknd-reddit-ama-interview.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223918/https://www.okayplayer.com/news/the-weeknd-reddit-ama-interview.html |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |website=[[Okayplayer]]|mode=cs2}}</ref> and is also fluent in [[French language|French]], as he attended a [[French immersion in Canada|French immersion school]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=April 8, 2020 |title=The Weeknd Opens Up About His Past, Turning 30 and Getting Vulnerable on 'After Hours' |url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/the-weeknd-exclusive-interview-after-hours-1234573754/ |access-date=March 22, 2022 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US |archive-date=April 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408144604/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/the-weeknd-exclusive-interview-after-hours-1234573754/ |url-status=live|mode=cs2 }}</ref> He was further educated at [[West Hill Collegiate Institute]] and [[Birchmount Park Collegiate Institute]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Scarborough native The Weeknd scores seven Grammy nominations |url=https://www.toronto.com/news-story/6163335-scarborough-native-the-weeknd-scores-seven-grammy-nominations/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223944/https://www.toronto.com/news-story/6163335-scarborough-native-the-weeknd-scores-seven-grammy-nominations/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Tara | last=Hatherly | date=December 7, 2015 | work=[[Metroland Media Group]]}}</ref>

At seventeen, Tesfaye dropped out of school and relocated to an apartment in the neighbourhood of [[Parkdale, Toronto|Parkdale]] with two friends, one of whom is [[La Mar Taylor]]—his best friend and now [[creative director]].<ref name="veryown">{{Cite news |last=Mistry |first=Anupa |title=Why The Weeknd is truly Toronto's very own |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/toronto/why-the-weeknd-is-truly-torontos-very-own/article27053702/ |url-status=live |date=October 30, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223920/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/toronto/why-the-weeknd-is-truly-torontos-very-own/article27053702/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021|mode=cs2}}</ref> Living a [[Hedonism|hedonistic]] lifestyle with his friends,<ref name="Biggest" /><ref name="Know">{{Cite news |last1=Wagstaff |first1=Keith |last2=Swanson |first2=David |title=10 Things You Should Know About the Weeknd |url=https://www.gq.com/story/5-things-you-should-know-about-the-weeknd |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704214239/https://www.gq.com/story/5-things-you-should-know-about-the-weeknd |archive-date=July 4, 2018 | date=October 26, 2015 |website=[[GQ]]|mode=cs2}}</ref> Tesfaye adopted his stage name because he left home on a weekend.<ref name="Went" /> He removed the last 'e' in 'weekend' to avoid [[trademark]] issues with the Canadian [[pop rock]] band [[The Weekend (Canadian band)|the Weekend]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Caramanica |first=Jon |author-link=Jon Caramanica |date=July 20, 2021 |title=Can the Weeknd Turn Himself Into the Biggest Pop Star in the World? - The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/magazine/can-the-weeknd-turn-himself-into-the-biggest-pop-star-in-the-world.html |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720072448/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/magazine/can-the-weeknd-turn-himself-into-the-biggest-pop-star-in-the-world.html |archive-date=July 20, 2021 |access-date=September 28, 2021 |magazine=[[The New York Times Magazine]] |mode=cs2}}</ref> He has also experienced homelessness and was incarcerated on several occasions during this time, which encouraged him to "smarten up, to focus".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://people.com/music/the-weeknd-on-overcoming-stage-fright/|title=The Weeknd Reveals How His Fans Helped Him Overcome Stage Fright|date=December 12, 2016|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|first=Lindsay|last=Kimble|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240310182618/https://people.com/music/the-weeknd-on-overcoming-stage-fright/|archive-date=March 10, 2024|url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/dec/03/the-weeknd-abel-tesfaye-interview-music-tom-lamont|title=The Weeknd: 'Drugs were a crutch for me'|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=December 3, 2016|access-date=March 11, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231129120504/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/dec/03/the-weeknd-abel-tesfaye-interview-music-tom-lamont|archive-date=November 29, 2023|url-status=live|mode=cs2|first=Tom|last=Lamont}}</ref> During this time, Tesfaye frequently engaged in drug use, including substances such as [[ketamine]], [[cocaine]], [[MDMA]], [[Psilocybin mushroom|magic mushrooms]], and [[Cold medicine|cough syrup]],<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Luchina |author-link=Luchina Fisher |date=December 5, 2016 |title=The Weeknd Opens Up About His 'Dark' Past |website=[[ABC News (United States)|ABC News]] |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/weeknd-opens-dark-past/story?id=43987671 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107224046/https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/weeknd-opens-dark-past/story?id=43987671 |archive-date=January 7, 2021|mode=cs2}}</ref> stating that drugs were a "crutch" for him when he wrote music.<ref>{{Cite news |date=December 3, 2016 |title=The Weeknd opens up about 'heavy' drug use |website=[[NME]] |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/weeknd-opens-drug-use-1888046 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107224108/https://www.nme.com/news/music/weeknd-opens-drug-use-1888046 |archive-date=January 7, 2021|mode=cs2|first=Nick|last=Levine|access-date=March 11, 2024}}</ref> Before releasing music under his current stage name, he went under the alias 'Kin Kane', as part of a hip-hop duo called 'Bulleez n Nerdz',<ref name="Fantasy3" /> and was part of a production team called 'the Noise'.<ref>{{cite web |last=Breihan |first=Tom |date=May 25, 2011 |title=Hear Unreleased Early Tracks From the Weeknd |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/42635-hear-unreleased-early-tracks-from-the-weeknd/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240220203713/https://pitchfork.com/news/42635-hear-unreleased-early-tracks-from-the-weeknd/ |archive-date=February 20, 2024 |access-date=February 20, 2024 |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |mode=cs2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=March 22, 2012 |title=How the Producer of the Weeknd's Breakout Tracks Got Majorly Screwed |url=https://www.vice.com/en/article/7bexag/how-the-producer-of-the-weeknds-breakout-tracks-got-majorly-screwed |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224110035/http://www.vice.com/read/how-the-producer-of-the-weeknds-breakout-tracks-got-majorly-screwed |archive-date=December 24, 2012 |access-date=September 28, 2021 |language=en |magazine=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |mode=cs2}}</ref>

=== 2009–2014: ''Trilogy'' and ''Kiss Land'' ===
In August 2009, Tesfaye began anonymously releasing music on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=December 27, 2019|title=10-Year High: The Weeknd's Game-Changing Decade|url=https://www.papermag.com/the-weeknd-2010s-career-2642233169.html|mode=cs2|access-date=December 20, 2021|website=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|language=en|archive-date=March 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220308153108/https://www.papermag.com/the-weeknd-2010s-career-2642233169.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Everything We Know About The Weeknd Before He Blew Up|url=https://www.complex.com/music/everything-we-know-about-the-weeknd-before-he-blew-up/|access-date=December 20, 2021|website=[[Complex Networks|Complex]]|archive-date=March 15, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220315044609/https://www.complex.com/music/everything-we-know-about-the-weeknd-before-he-blew-up/|url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref> The following year, he met the producer Jeremy Rose at a party. Rose asked Tesfaye if he wanted to work together as a dark R&B project after hearing him freestyle over an instrumental. After creating multiple songs and parting ways due to creative differences, Tesfaye was allowed to use the songs they made together under the condition that Rose received production credits.<ref name="Screwed">{{Cite news |last=McGuire |first=Patrick |date=March 22, 2012 |title=How the Producer of The Weeknd's Breakout Tracks Got Majorly Screwed |work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |url=https://www.vice.com/read/how-the-producer-of-the-weeknds-breakout-tracks-got-majorly-screwed |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224110035/http://www.vice.com/read/how-the-producer-of-the-weeknds-breakout-tracks-got-majorly-screwed |archive-date=December 24, 2012|mode=cs2}}</ref> In December 2010, Tesfaye uploaded "What You Need", "Loft Music" and "[[The Morning (The Weeknd song)|The Morning]]" to YouTube under the username "xoxxxoooxo".<ref name="nytimes">{{Cite news |last=Caramanica |first=Jon | author-link=Jon Caramanica |title=Screams That Charmed, and Other Overlooked Highlights |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/02/arts/music/02playlist.html |url-status=live |date=December 31, 2010 | url-access=limited |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210094135/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/02/arts/music/02playlist.html?_r=4&ref=music |archive-date=February 10, 2015|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Stewart |first=Allison |date=March 14, 2011 |title=Singles File: Da Phuture, The Weeknd, Fever Ray |mode=cs2|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/03/14/AR2011031403984.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131208064202/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/03/14/AR2011031403984.html |archive-date=December 8, 2013}}</ref> His identity remained undisclosed initially. These songs gained attention online and were later acknowledged in a blog post by the rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]].<ref name=Screwed/><ref>{{Cite news |last=Shepherd |first=Julianne Escobedo |date=March 23, 2011 |title=Love and Other Drugs: The Weeknd's Altered-State R&B |url=https://www.thirteen.org/riffcity/music/love-and-other-drugs-the-weeknds-altered-state-rb/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129222613/https://www.thirteen.org/riffcity/music/love-and-other-drugs-the-weeknds-altered-state-rb/ |archive-date=November 29, 2020 |publisher=[[WNET]]|mode=cs2}}</ref> The songs subsequently received coverage from various media outlets, including [[Pitchfork (website)|''Pitchfork'']] and ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fitzmaurice |first=Larry |title=The Weeknd – ''What You Need'' |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/12131-the-weeknd-what-you-need/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326174005/http://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/12131-what-you-need |archive-date=March 26, 2011 |date=March 4, 2011 | website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|mode=cs2}}</ref>

In 2011, Tesfaye met music executives [[Wassim Slaiby|Wassim "Sal" Slaiby]] and [[Amir Esmailian|Amir "Cash" Esmailian]], with whom, along with Taylor, he founded the [[XO (record label)|XO]] record label.<ref name=":0">{{Cite magazine|title=The Weeknd on the Crew That Boosted Him From 'Basically Homeless' to the Super Bowl|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/enterprise/9516909/the-weeknd-xo-records-billboard-cover-story-interview-2021|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 28, 2021|access-date=June 8, 2021|mode=cs2|archive-date=June 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210608184025/https://www.billboard.com/articles/enterprise/9516909/the-weeknd-xo-records-billboard-cover-story-interview-2021|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 21, Tesfaye released his debut mixtape, ''[[House of Balloons]]'',{{efn|Multiple sources:<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Kameir|first1=Rawiya|last2=Hockley-Smith|first2=Sam|last3=Mistry|first3=Anupa|date=March 21, 2016|title=How House of Balloons Changed R&B|work=[[The Fader]]|url=https://www.thefader.com/2016/03/21/house-of-balloons-rountable-the-weeknd|mode=cs2|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223914/https://www.thefader.com/2016/03/21/house-of-balloons-rountable-the-weeknd|archive-date=January 7, 2021|quote=Five years since its veiled release, a conversation about The Weeknd's debut and its influence on contemporary pop music...The album was documenting a nascent scene that has gone on to shift the cultural paradigm of Toronto, and it did so through a sound that has had a lasting effect on contemporary pop music.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Ramirez |first=Erika |title=Say Hello to The Weeknd, Drake Co-Signs |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/genre/hip-hop//2011/03/21/say-hello-to-the-weeknd-drake-co-signs/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151012012132/http://rapfix.mtv.com/2011/03/21/say-hello-to-the-weeknd-drake-co-signs/ |archive-date=October 12, 2015 |date=March 21, 2011 | website=[[MTV News]]|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cbcmusic.ca/posts/17548/cohen-gould-buffy-25-best-canadian-debut-albums | title=25 best Canadian debut albums ever | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906183203/http://www.cbcmusic.ca/posts/17548/cohen-gould-buffy-25-best-canadian-debut-albums | archive-date=September 6, 2017 | work=[[CBC Music]] | date=June 16, 2017|mode=cs2}}</ref>}} which featured production from [[Illangelo]] and [[Doc McKinney]]. The mixtape also included tracks produced by Rose, although he did not receive production credits.<ref name="Screwed" /> ''House of Balloons'' was named as one of the ten shortlisted nominees for the [[2011 Polaris Music Prize]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Polaris Music Prize |url=https://polarismusicprize.ca/album/house-of-balloons/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409053023/http://www.polarismusicprize.ca/2011/ |archive-date=April 9, 2014 |website=[[Polaris Music Prize]]|mode=cs2}}</ref>

Tesfaye started working with Drake in May 2011, eventually earning a spot at the latter's [[OVO Fest]] on July 31.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fitzmaurice |first=Larry |date=July 3, 2011 |title=The Weeknd to Play Drake's OVO Festival |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/42716-the-weeknd-to-play-drakes-ovo-festival/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223855/https://pitchfork.com/news/42716-the-weeknd-to-play-drakes-ovo-festival/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |access-date=March 11, 2024 |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |mode=cs2}}</ref> In July 2011, Tesfaye held his first live performance at the [[Mod Club Theatre]] in Toronto.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ritchie |first=Kevin |date=July 25, 2011 |title=The Weeknd's perfect premiere |work=[[NOW Toronto]] |url=https://nowtoronto.com/the-weeknds-perfect-premiere |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111222100021/http://www.nowtoronto.com/daily/music/story.cfm?content=181922 |archive-date=December 22, 2011|access-date=March 3, 2011|mode=cs2}}</ref>  He also participated in concerts hosted by the Black Student Association at the [[University of Toronto]].<ref name="before">{{Cite magazine | url=https://www.complex.com/music/everything-we-know-about-the-weeknd-before-he-blew-up/ | title=Everything We Know About The Weeknd Before He Blew Up | first=Calum | last=Marsh | magazine=[[Complex Networks|Complex]] | date=February 16, 2021 | access-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-date=March 15, 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220315044609/https://www.complex.com/music/everything-we-know-about-the-weeknd-before-he-blew-up/ | url-status=live|mode=cs2 }}</ref> On August 18, Tesfaye released his second mixtape, ''[[Thursday (album)|Thursday]]'', which garnered usually positive reviews.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Diver |first=Mike |title=BBC - Music - Review of The Weeknd - Thursday |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/jgq4/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220710025008/https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/jgq4/ |archive-date=July 10, 2022 |access-date=September 28, 2021 |publisher=[[BBC]] |language=en-GB |mode=cs2}}</ref> Tesfaye contributed to four songs on Drake's second studio album, ''[[Take Care (album)|Take Care]]'', released on November 15, as a songwriter, producer and a featured artist on the album's seventh single, "[[Crew Love]]".<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Berry|first=Peter A.|date=November 16, 2017|title=Drake Sets The Record Straight On How Much The Weeknd Wrote On Take Care Album|magazine=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/11/drake-the-weeknd-wrote-take-care/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223930/https://www.xxlmag.com/drake-the-weeknd-wrote-take-care/|archive-date=January 7, 2021|mode=cs2}}</ref> He released his third mixtape, ''[[Echoes of Silence]]'', on December 21. It was a longlisted nominee for the [[2012 Polaris Music Prize]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dunlevy |first=T'Cha |date=March 23, 2012 |title=365 days of Weeknd: We chart Abel Tesfaye's rise to fame a year after House of Balloons |url=https://nationalpost.com/entertainment/365-days-of-weeknd-we-chart-abel-tesfayes-rise-to-fame-a-year-after-house-of-balloons |url-status=live |archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20120321220120/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/03/20/365%2Ddays%2Dof%2Dweeknd%2Dwe%2Dchart%2Dabel%2Dtesfayes%2Drise%2Dto%2Dfame%2Da%2Dyear%2Dafter%2Dhouse%2Dof%2Dballoons/ |archive-date=March 21, 2012 |access-date=March 11, 2024 |newspaper=[[National Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Mudhar |first=Raju |date=June 14, 2012 |title=Polaris Prize long list includes lots of Toronto bands |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2012/06/14/polaris_prize_long_list_includes_lots_of_toronto_bands.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103215956/http://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2012/06/14/polaris_prize_long_list_includes_lots_of_toronto_bands.html |archive-date=November 3, 2014 |access-date=September 28, 2021 |newspaper=[[The Toronto Star]] |language=en-CA |issn=0319-0781 |mode=cs2}}</ref>[[File:The Weeknd by David Hwang.jpg|thumb|alt=The Weeknd wearing a button-up, sleeveless shirt covering a normal black t-shirt. He is performing on a stage, singing into a microphone, with palm trees in the background.|Tesfaye performing at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] in 2012]]
In April 2012, Tesfaye began performing at more shows, such as the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella Festival]],<ref name=debut>{{Cite news |last=Snapes |first=Laura |title=Abel Tesfaye makes his U.S. debut |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/46157-watch-the-weeknds-entire-coachella-set/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223903/https://pitchfork.com/news/46157-watch-the-weeknds-entire-coachella-set/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |date=April 16, 2012 | website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|access-date=March 11, 2024|mode=cs2}}</ref> and two sold-out shows at the [[Bowery Ballroom]] in New York City.<ref name=debut/><ref>{{Cite news |last=Krishnamurthy |first=Sowmya |author-link=Sowmya Krishnamurthy |date=April 29, 2012 |title=The Weeknd Mesmerizes at Bowery Ballroom |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/the-weeknd-mesmerizes-at-bowery-ballroom-20120429 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120526210653/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/the-weeknd-mesmerizes-at-bowery-ballroom-20120429 |archive-date=May 26, 2012 | magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] | url-access=subscription|mode=cs2}}</ref> He also performed at various European festivals, such as [[Primavera Sound]] in Spain and Portugal<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://pitchfork.com/news/45598-the-weeknd-to-headline-pitchfork-stage-at-primavera/ | title=The Weeknd to Headline Pitchfork Stage at Primavera | first=Carrie | last=Battan | work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] | date=March 1, 2012 | access-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-date=July 16, 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220716154744/https://pitchfork.com/news/45598-the-weeknd-to-headline-pitchfork-stage-at-primavera/ | url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref> and the [[Wireless Festival]] in the United Kingdom.{{efn|Multiple sources:<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lough |first=Kate |date=May 31, 2012 |title=Wireless Festival 2012 |work=[[London Evening Standard]] |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/wireless-festival-2012-7804424.html |access-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-date=July 12, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220712094355/https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/wireless-festival-2012-7804424.html |url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |date=March 27, 2012 |title=The Weeknd, Chiddy Bang & More for Wireless 2012 |magazine=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]] |url=https://diymag.com/archive/the-weeknd-chiddy-bang-more-for-wireless-2012 |access-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-date=July 12, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220712094417/https://diymag.com/archive/the-weeknd-chiddy-bang-more-for-wireless-2012 |url-status=dead|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref name=covers>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd covers Michael Jackson as he plays his debut UK show |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/weekend-3-1280196 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223930/https://www.nme.com/news/music/weekend-3-1280196 |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Tom | last=Goodwyn | date=June 8, 2012| magazine=[[NME]] | url-status=live|access-date=March 11, 2024|mode=cs2}}</ref>}} In September, Tesfaye signed with [[Republic Records]]; XO was assumed as a [[subsidiary|subsidiary label]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Hampp |first=Andrew |title=The Weeknd & Reps Talk Clearing Samples, Touring For 'Trilogy' Release |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/474219/the-weeknd-reps-talk-clearing-samples-touring-for-trilogy-release |url-status=live | magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223925/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/474219/the-weeknd-reps-talk-clearing-samples-touring-for-trilogy-release |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |date=November 12, 2012|mode=cs2}}</ref> That same month, he embarked on his first concert tour, the Fall Tour, which included his own headlining shows and some opening shows for the English band [[Florence and the Machine]]. The tour was performed in North America in September to November 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/weeknd_schedules_more_canadian_dates_on_north_american_fall_tour|title=The Weeknd Schedules More Canadian Dates on North American Fall Tour|first=Alex|last=Hudson|date=August 14, 2012|access-date=March 11, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210801174448/https://exclaim.ca/music/article/weeknd_schedules_more_canadian_dates_on_north_american_fall_tour|archive-date=August 1, 2021|mode=cs2|url-status=live|magazine=[[Exclaim!]]}}</ref>

On November 13, 2012, Tesfaye released ''[[Trilogy (The Weeknd album)|Trilogy]]'', a compilation album comprising re-mixed and remastered versions of his 2011 mixtapes, and three additional tracks.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Diver |first=Mike |title=The Weeknd Trilogy Review |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/gr5c/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240407011734/http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/gr5c/ |archive-date=April 7, 2024 |date=November 13, 2012 |website=[[BBC Music]]|access-date=March 11, 2024|mode=cs2}}</ref> The album debuted at number four on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with first-week sales of 86,000 copies,<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=October 10, 2012 |title=One Direction Tops Billboard 200 Chart, 'Twilight' Debuts at No. 3 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474052/one-direction-tops-billboard-200-chart-twilight-debuts-at-no-3 |url-status=live |location=[[Los Angeles]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224023649/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474052/one-direction-tops-billboard-200-chart-twilight-debuts-at-no-3 |archive-date=February 24, 2017 | magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|mode=cs2}}</ref> and has received [[RIAA certification|platinum]] certifications from the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) and double-platinum from [[Music Canada]].<ref name="RIAA">{{Cite web |title=Gold & Platinum Searchable Database |url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |access-date=September 16, 2017 |archive-date=June 26, 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626174049/http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php |url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Gold and Platinum Search |url=https://musiccanada.com/gold-platinum/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927064324/http://www.musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=Trilogy&sa=The+Weeknd&smt=0 |archive-date=September 27, 2013 |publisher=[[Music Canada]]|access-date=March 11, 2024|mode=cs2}}</ref> It also earned Tesfaye a nomination for the [[Sound of...|Sound of 2013]] poll award by [[BBC]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sound of 2013 Profiles: The Weeknd |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p010q6bc/profiles/theweeknd |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121213061703/http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p010q6bc/profiles/theweeknd |archive-date=December 13, 2012 |date=December 9, 2012 |publisher=[[BBC]]|mode=cs2}}</ref>

[[File:The Weeknd at Massey Hall October 17, 2013 amber lighting.jpg|thumb|left|alt=The picture depicts Tesfaye performing, with the lights giving the image an orange environment. In the background, there is a drum set.|Tesfaye performing at [[Massey Hall]] in October 2013]]

On May 17, 2013, Tesfaye released the [[Kiss Land (song)|title track]] to his debut studio album, ''[[Kiss Land]]''<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Nostro |first=Lauren |title=Listen: The Weeknd "Kiss Land" |magazine=[[Complex Networks|Complex]] |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2013/05/listen-the-weeknd-kiss-land |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124205738/https://www.complex.com/music/2013/05/listen-the-weeknd-kiss-land |archive-date=November 24, 2020 |date=May 16, 2013|access-date=March 11, 2024|mode=cs2}}</ref> and announced the album's release date of September 10.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Williott |first=Carl |date=July 22, 2013 |title=The Weeknd Unveils 'Kiss Land' Release Date & Cover Artwork |url=https://www.idolator.com/7472491/the-weeknd-kiss-land-release-date-cover-artwork |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |access-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029160534/https://www.idolator.com/7472491/the-weeknd-kiss-land-release-date-cover-artwork |url-status=live|mode=cs2}}</ref> Upon its release, the album debuted at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 with 96,000 copies<ref>{{Cite magazine | first=Keith | last=Caulfield |date=December 1, 2012 |title=Keith Urban Edges The Weeknd for No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5695587/keith-urban-edges-the-weeknd-for-no-1-debut-on-billboard-200 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130919013240/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5695587/keith-urban-edges-the-weeknd-for-no-1-debut-on-billboard-200 |archive-date=September 19, 2013 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|mode=cs2}}</ref> and received generally positive reviews from music critics.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kiss Land Reviews |url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/kiss-land/the-weeknd |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223922/https://www.metacritic.com/music/kiss-land/the-weeknd |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |access-date=March 11, 2024|website=[[Metacritic]]|mode=cs2}}</ref> Tesfaye further promoted the album with a fall tour that occurred in North America and England in September to November 2013.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://pitchfork.com/news/51422-the-weeknd-announces-big-fall-tour-kiss-land-out-late-summer/ | title=The Weeknd Announces Big Fall Tour, Kiss Land Out Late Summer | first=Carrie | last=Battan | work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] | date=July 8, 2013 | access-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523145638/https://pitchfork.com/news/51422-the-weeknd-announces-big-fall-tour-kiss-land-out-late-summer/ | url-status=live | mode=cs2}}</ref> Between November 6 and 13, he served as an opening act for [[Justin Timberlake]] during [[The 20/20 Experience World Tour]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Payne |first=Chris |date=November 4, 2013 |title=The Weeknd To Open For Justin Timberlake On '20/20 Experience' Tour |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/5778176/the-weeknd-to-open-for-justin-timberlake-on-2020-experience-tour |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223923/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/5778176/the-weeknd-to-open-for-justin-timberlake-on-2020-experience-tour |archive-date=January 7, 2021|mode=cs2}}</ref> He also contributed two songs to the [[The Hunger Games: Catching Fire – Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|soundtrack]] for the 2013 film ''[[The Hunger Games: Catching Fire]]'', "Devil May Cry" and the soundtrack's second single, "[[Elastic Heart]]" with [[Sia]] and [[Diplo]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Hakimian |first=Rob |date=November 19, 2013 |title=Album Review: Various Artists – The Hunger Games: Catching Fire Soundtrack |url=https://consequence.net/2013/11/album-review-various-artists-the-hunger-games-catching-fire-soundtrack/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211061733/https://consequenceofsound.net/2013/11/album-review-various-artists-the-hunger-games-catching-fire-soundtrack/ |archive-date=December 11, 2018 |magazine=[[Consequence (publication)|Consequence]]|mode=cs2}}</ref>

In February 2014, Tesfaye released a remix of "[[Drunk in Love]]" from [[Beyoncé]]'s [[Beyoncé (album)|eponymous studio album]],<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Hooton|first=Christopher|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/listen-the-weeknd-enters-beyonce-drunk-in-love-remix-battle-with-kanye-west-and-diplo-9133498.html|title=Listen: The Weeknd enters Beyonce Drunk in Love remix battle with Kanye West and Diplo|magazine=[[The Independent]]|date=February 17, 2014|access-date=May 2, 2024|archive-date=May 2, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502064118/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/listen-the-weeknd-enters-beyonce-drunk-in-love-remix-battle-with-kanye-west-and-diplo-9133498.html|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Ty Dolla Sign]]'s "[[Or Nah (Ty Dolla Sign song)|Or Nah]]".<ref>{{cite web|last=Pelly|first=Jen|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/54068-listen-the-weeknd-remixes-ty-dolla-igns-or-nah/|title=Listen: The Weeknd remixes Ty Dolla Sign's "Or Nah"|website=Pitchfork|date=February 21, 2014|access-date=May 2, 2024|archive-date=May 2, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502064121/https://pitchfork.com/news/54068-listen-the-weeknd-remixes-ty-dolla-igns-or-nah/|url-status=live}}</ref> He announced the [[King of the Fall Tour]] in June 2014, a 4-city tour of North America between September and October and was supported by [[Schoolboy Q]] and [[Jhené Aiko]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 26, 2014 |title=The Weeknd touring w/ Schoolboy Q & Jhene Aiko, playing Barclays Center (dates); SBQ played Central Park |url=https://www.brooklynvegan.com/the-weeknd-tour-1/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924044926/http://www.brooklynvegan.com/archives/2014/06/the_weeknd_tour_1.html |archive-date=September 24, 2014 |website=[[BrooklynVegan]]}}</ref> In promotion of the tour, he released the songs "[[King of the Fall]]" and "[[Often]]" in July of that year.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Bowe|first=Miles|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1693315/the-weeknd-king-of-the-fall/news/|title=The Weeknd – "King Of The Fall"|magazine=Stereogum|date=July 21, 2014|access-date=May 2, 2024|archive-date=May 2, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502064118/https://www.stereogum.com/1693315/the-weeknd-king-of-the-fall/news/|url-status=live}}</ref> On August 25, Tesfaye collaborated with [[Ariana Grande]] on the song "[[Love Me Harder]]" from Grande's second studio album ''[[My Everything (Ariana Grande album)|My Everything]]''. It was later released on September 30 as the fourth single from the album, and peaked at number seven on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=October 3, 2014 |title=Ariana Grande and The Weeknd Team Up In 'Love Me Harder' Video |work=[[Rap-Up]] |url=https://www.rap-up.com/2014/10/03/first-look-ariana-grande-the-weeknd-love-me-harder-video/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141005205143/http://www.rap-up.com/2014/10/03/first-look-ariana-grande-the-weeknd-love-me-harder-video/ |archive-date=October 5, 2014}}</ref> On December 23, Tesfaye released the song "[[Earned It]]" from the [[Fifty Shades of Grey (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for ''[[Fifty Shades of Grey (film)|Fifty Shades of Grey]]'' (2015). The single, which peaked at number three on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, earned Tesfaye his first [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] nomination for [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Cox |first=Jamieson |date=February 28, 2016 |title=Oscars 2016: Watch The Weeknd reenact his sultry video for Earned It |work=[[The Verge]] |url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/2/28/11130062/the-weeknd-earned-it-performance-watch-academy-awards-2016 |access-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-date=April 18, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230418071407/https://www.theverge.com/2016/2/28/11130062/the-weeknd-earned-it-performance-watch-academy-awards-2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> The song won [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Performance|Best R&B Performance]] and was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Song|Best R&B Song]] and [[Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media|Best Song Written for Visual Media]] at the [[58th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Grammys 2016: The Weeknd Wins Two Awards|url=https://people.com/awards/grammys-2016-the-weeknd-wins-two-awards/|access-date=September 28, 2021|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|archive-date=September 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210929004222/https://people.com/awards/grammys-2016-the-weeknd-wins-two-awards/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2015–2016: ''Beauty Behind the Madness''===
[[File:The Weeknd Bumbershoot 2015.jpg|thumb|upright|Tesfaye performing at [[Bumbershoot]] 2015]]
On May 27, 2015, Tesfaye released the second single from ''Beauty Behind the Madness'', "[[The Hills (song)|The Hills]]".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lockett |first=Dee |title=The Weeknd Returns With 'The Hills,' Which Probably Isn't About Lauren Conrad |url=https://www.vulture.com/2015/05/weeknd-debuts-new-song-the-hills.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223930/https://www.vulture.com/2015/05/weeknd-debuts-new-song-the-hills.html |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | date=May 27, 2015 |website=[[Vulture.com]] |ref=vulture-hills}}</ref> The single debuted at number twenty on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, and peaked at number one, becoming Tesfaye's second number-one single, following "[[Can't Feel My Face]]", which had reached the number one position before it. In June 2019, "The Hills" was [[RIAA certification|certified diamond]] by the RIAA, marking Tesfaye's first diamond-certified record.<ref>{{Cite news |last=McIntyre |first=Hugh |date=June 28, 2019 |title=The Weeknd's No. 1 Hit 'The Hills' Becomes His First Diamond-Certified Single |work=[[Forbes]] |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2019/06/28/the-weeknds-no-1-hit-the-hills-becomes-his-first-diamond-certified-single/ |url-access=limited |access-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518195601/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2019/06/28/the-weeknds-no-1-hit-the-hills-becomes-his-first-diamond-certified-single/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Lamare |first=Carl |date=June 28, 2019 |title=The Weeknd's 'The Hills' Certified Diamond: Exclusive |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8517989/the-weeknd-the-hills-diamond |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223924/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8517989/the-weeknd-the-hills-diamond |archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref>

In June 2015, after winning the Centric Award at the [[BET Awards 2015|BET Awards]], Tesfaye performed "Earned It" with [[Alicia Keys]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Beauchemin |first=Molly |title=Janelle Monáe Performs "Yoga", The Weeknd Performs "Earned It" with Alicia Keys at the BET Awards |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/60165-janelle-monae-performs-yoga-the-weeknd-performs-earned-it-with-alicia-keys-at-the-bet-awards/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223929/https://pitchfork.com/news/60165-janelle-monae-performs-yoga-the-weeknd-performs-earned-it-with-alicia-keys-at-the-bet-awards/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | date=June 28, 2015 |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref> On June 8, he released the song "[[Can't Feel My Face]]" as the album's third single. The track was previously leaked in May, but was released as a single following a performance by Tesfaye at the [[Apple Worldwide Developers Conference]].<ref name="RS1">{{Cite news |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |date=June 8, 2015 |title=Hear The Weeknd's Funky New Song 'Can't Feel My Face' |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-the-weeknds-funky-new-song-cant-feel-my-face-20150608 |url-status=live |url-access=limited |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618031403/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-the-weeknds-funky-new-song-cant-feel-my-face-20150608 |archive-date=June 18, 2015}}</ref> The single debuted at number twenty-four on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, and peaked at number one, making it Tesfaye's third top 10 hit and his first number-one song in the United States.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |title=Wiz Khalifa No. 1 on Hot 100 'Again,' Selena Gomez Debuts at No. 9 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6613247/wiz-khalifa-no-1-hot-100-selena-gomez-debuts |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223910/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6613247/wiz-khalifa-no-1-hot-100-selena-gomez-debuts |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |date=July 1, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Trust |first=Gary |title=The Weeknd Tops Hot 100 With 'Can't Feel My Face,' One Direction Debuts at No. 3 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6656820/the-weeknd-no-1-hot-100-cant-feel-my-face-one-direction-drag-me-down |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223919/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6656820/the-weeknd-no-1-hot-100-cant-feel-my-face-one-direction-drag-me-down |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |date=August 10, 2015| magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> The song was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] and [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Solo Performance|Best Pop Solo Performance]] at the 58th Annual Grammy Awards.<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Grammy Nominations 2016: See the Full List of Nominees|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/6785974/grammy-nominations-2016-full-list|access-date=September 28, 2021|magazine=Billboard|date=December 7, 2015|language=en|archive-date=December 10, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151210021119/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/6785974/grammy-nominations-2016-full-list|url-status=live}}</ref> He occupied all three slots on ''Billboard's'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart simultaneously with the aforementioned singles, becoming the first artist in history to accomplish this.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6633631/weeknd-entire-top-three-hot-rb-songs-chart | title=The Weeknd Is First Artist to Own Entire Top Three on Hot R&B Songs Chart | first=Amaya | last=Mendizabal | magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date=July 15, 2015 | access-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-date=May 16, 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516023205/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6633631/weeknd-entire-top-three-hot-rb-songs-chart | url-status=live }}</ref> He was also unveiled as one of the musical faces of the streaming service Apple Music, alongside Drake.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Apple's new musical faces – Drake and The Weeknd |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/afp-apples-new-musical-faces---drake-and-the-weeknd-2015-6 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304052552/https://www.businessinsider.com/afp-apples-new-musical-faces---drake-and-the-weeknd-2015-6 |archive-date=March 4, 2021 | agency=[[Agence France-Presse]] | work=[[Business Insider]] | date=June 8, 2015}}</ref> During the [[2015 MTV Video Music Awards]], Apple debuted a two-part promotional commercial featuring Tesfaye, which had a guest appearance from [[John Travolta]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Latest Apple Music ads debut during MTV VMAs, feature The Weeknd & playlists |url=https://appleinsider.com/articles/15/08/31/latest-apple-music-ads-debut-during-mtv-vmas-feature-the-weeknd-playlists |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223931/https://appleinsider.com/articles/15/08/31/latest-apple-music-ads-debut-during-mtv-vmas-feature-the-weeknd-playlists |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | date=August 31, 2015}}</ref> In July, Tesfaye headlined the inaugural FVDED in the Park festival in [[Surrey, British Columbia]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=December 19, 2017 |title=Deadmau5 & The Weeknd headline FVDED IN THE PARK 2015 |work=[[Daily Hive]] |url=https://dailyhive.com/vancouver/fvded-in-the-park-2015-lineup-surrey |access-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-date=May 18, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518195601/https://dailyhive.com/vancouver/fvded-in-the-park-2015-lineup-surrey |url-status=live }}</ref> On June 29, Tesfaye was featured on [[Meek Mill]]'s second studio album ''[[Dreams Worth More Than Money]]'' (2015), on the track "Pullin' Up".<ref>{{Cite news |title=Meek Mill Reveals 'Dreams Worth More Than Money' Features |url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.34353/title.meek-mill-reveals-dreams-worth-more-than-money-features |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130211403/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.34353/title.meek-mill-reveals-dreams-worth-more-than-money-features |archive-date=November 30, 2019 | first=Danielle | last=Harling | date=June 22, 2015 | website=[[HipHopDX]]}}</ref>

''[[Beauty Behind the Madness]]'', Tesfaye's second studio album, was released on August 28, 2015, and debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200, earning 412,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s in its first week.<ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd's 'Beauty Behind the Madness' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6685947/the-weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-debuts-at-no-1-billboard-200-charts |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180323161116/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6685947/the-weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-debuts-at-no-1-billboard-200-charts |archive-date=March 23, 2018 |first=Keith | last=Caulfield | date=September 6, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd spends third week at No. 1 on Billboard 200 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6700714/the-weeknd-billboard-200-third-week-no-1 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223911/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6700714/the-weeknd-billboard-200-third-week-no-1 |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |first=Keith | last=Caulfield | date=September 20, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> It reached the top 10 in over ten countries and reached number one in Canada, Australia, Norway, and the United Kingdom.<ref>{{Cite web |title=ARIA Albums : The Weeknd Takes Top Spot On Australian Chart |url=http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-albums-the-weeknd-takes-top-spot-on-australian-chart-20150905 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130063137/http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-albums-the-weeknd-takes-top-spot-on-australian-chart-20150905 |archive-date=November 30, 2020 | first=Gavin | last=Ryan | date=September 5, 2015 | work=[[Noise11]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Top 20 Albums |url=https://musiccanada.com/charts/2015-09-21/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927193747/http://musiccanada.com/charts/#albums |archive-date=September 27, 2015 | website=[[Music Canada]]}}</ref> The album was promoted by Tesfaye headlining various summer music festivals, including [[Lollapalooza]], the [[Hard (music festival)|Hard Summer Music Festival]], and the [[Bumbershoot]] Festival.<ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd's new album is coming Aug. 28 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2015/07/10/weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-august-28-release/29961285/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713235618/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2015/07/10/weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-august-28-release/29961285/ |archive-date=July 13, 2015 | first=Brian | last=Mansfield | author-link=Brian Mansfield | date=July 10, 2015 |website=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> He announced [[The Madness Fall Tour]], his first large-scale tour across the United States, which began in November, and concluded in December.<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Weeknd announces The Madness Fall Tour |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/60875-the-weeknd-announces-the-madness-fall-tour/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223940/https://pitchfork.com/news/60875-the-weeknd-announces-the-madness-fall-tour/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Jeremy | last=Gordon | date=August 20, 2015 |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd Announces The Madness Fall Tour With Travi$ Scott, Halsey & Banks |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6671102/the-weeknd-the-madness-fall-tour-dates |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150823233024/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6671102/the-weeknd-the-madness-fall-tour-dates |archive-date=August 23, 2015 | first=Paley | last=Martin | date=August 21, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> The album was certified double platinum in the U.S., and sold 1.5 million copies worldwide.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.complex.com/music/2016/08/the-weeknd-two-guinness-world-records | title=The Weeknd Now Holds Two Guinness World Records | first=Jessie | last=Morris | work=[[Complex Networks]] | date=August 30, 2016 | access-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523145638/https://www.complex.com/music/2016/08/the-weeknd-two-guinness-world-records | url-status=live }}</ref> It was the most-streamed album in 2015, with over 60 million streams,<ref>{{Cite news |title=Spotify's Year in Music: Drake Most Streamed Artist, Major Lazer & DJ Snake Had Top Song |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6778065/spotify-year-music-lists-2015-drake-rihanna-major-lazer-ed-sheeran |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151202172539/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6778065/spotify-year-music-lists-2015-drake-rihanna-major-lazer-ed-sheeran |archive-date=December 2, 2015 | first=Marc | last=Schneider | date=December 1, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> and was ranked on multiple lists of albums of the year.<ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd, 'Beauty Behind the Madness' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-albums-of-2015-146153/the-weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-2-225077/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202125320/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/50-best-albums-of-2015-20151201/the-weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-20151130 |archive-date=December 2, 2016 | date=December 1, 2015 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref> The three singles that preceded the album were certified platinum in the United States.<ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd Doubles Up in Hot 100's Top Three |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6685989/the-weeknd-hot-100-top-three |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223928/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6685989/the-weeknd-hot-100-top-three |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Gary | last=Trust | date=September 8, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> The album won [[Grammy Award for Best Progressive R&B Album|Best Urban Contemporary Album]] and was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]] at the 58th Annual Grammy Awards.<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=See All the Winners of the 2016 Grammys|url=https://time.com/4224932/grammys-2016-winners-list-nominees-2/|access-date=September 28, 2021|magazine=Time|language=en|archive-date=February 27, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160227150427/https://time.com/hive.org/web/20160227150427/http://time.com/4224932/grammys-2016-winners-list-nominees/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On September 4, 2015, Tesfaye was featured on [[Travis Scott]]'s debut album ''[[Rodeo (Travis Scott album)|Rodeo]]'', on the track "Pray 4 Love".<ref>{{Cite news |title=Justin Bieber, Kanye West, The Weeknd, & more featuring on Travi$ Scott's 'Rodeo" album |url=https://www.inquisitr.com/2352303/justin-bieber-kanye-west-the-weeknd-more-featuring-on-travis-scott-s-rodeo-album/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117021132/https://www.inquisitr.com/2352303/justin-bieber-kanye-west-the-weeknd-more-featuring-on-travis-scott-s-rodeo-album/ |archive-date=January 17, 2021 | date=June 29, 2017 | website=[[Inquisitr]]}}</ref> On October 10, Tesfaye appeared on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' alongside actress [[Amy Schumer]], performing as the show's musical guest.<ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd & Demi Lovato Announced as 'SNL' Musical Guests |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6685066/weeknd-demi-lovato-snl-musical-guests |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223934/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6685066/weeknd-demi-lovato-snl-musical-guests |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Erin | last=Strecker | date=September 1, 2015 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref name="Perform">{{Cite news | title=Demi Lovato & The Weeknd To Perform On 'Saturday Night Live' This Season | url=https://www.idolator.com/7606572/demi-lovato-the-weeknd-perform-saturday-night-live-season-41 | first=Bianca | last=Gracie | date=September 1, 2015 | website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] | access-date=May 23, 2021 | archive-date=October 29, 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029160548/https://www.idolator.com/7606572/demi-lovato-the-weeknd-perform-saturday-night-live-season-41 | url-status=live }}</ref> This was his first performance on the show as a solo artist, after appearing with Ariana Grande to perform "Love Me Harder".<ref name="Perform" /> In November, he began his debut [[arena]] tour, [[The Madness Fall Tour]], which included shows at Toronto's [[Scotiabank Arena|Air Canada Centre]] and New York City's [[Madison Square Garden]]. On December 18, Tesfaye was featured on [[Belly (rapper)|Belly]]'s single "[[Might Not]]" from his eighth mixtape ''[[Up for Days|Up For Days]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Belly 'Might Not' (ft. The Weeknd) |url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/belly-might_not_ft_weeknd |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031072147/http://exclaim.ca/music/article/belly-might_not_ft_weeknd |archive-date=October 31, 2020 | first=Alex | last=Hudson | date=May 8, 2015 |website=[[Exclaim!]]}}</ref>

On February 14, 2016, Tesfaye was featured on [[Kanye West]]'s seventh studio album ''[[The Life of Pablo]]'' on the track "[[FML (song)|FML]]".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Guiducci|first=Mark|date=May 3, 2016|title=The Weeknd on Going From Indie R&B Enigma to the Pacesetting Prince of Pop|work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/the-weeknd-musician-profile-met-gala-performance|access-date=May 18, 2021|archive-date=May 18, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518212957/https://www.vogue.com/article/the-weeknd-musician-profile-met-gala-performance|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Hooton|first=Christopher|author-link=Christopher Hooton|date=February 12, 2016|title=The Life of Pablo tracklist: Kanye West's new album features Frank Ocean, The Weeknd and Young Thug|work=[[The Independent]]|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/life-pablo-tracklist-kanye-west-s-new-album-features-frank-ocean-weeknd-and-young-thug-a6869016.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220620/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/life-pablo-tracklist-kanye-west-s-new-album-features-frank-ocean-weeknd-and-young-thug-a6869016.html |archive-date=June 20, 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live}}</ref> It marked their second collaboration, with West previously writing and producing on Tesfaye's track "[[Tell Your Friends (song)|Tell Your Friends]]" from ''Beauty Behind the Madness''. On March 1, Tesfaye was featured on [[Future (rapper)|Future]]'s single "[[Low Life (song)|Low Life]]" from his fourth studio album ''[[Evol (Future album)|Evol]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Listen: The Weeknd Surprises Fans By Dropping Two New Songs! |url=https://www.kiss925.com/2015/12/27/listen-the-weeknd-surprises-fans-by-dropping-two-new-songs/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204083257/https://www.kiss925.com/2015/12/27/listen-the-weeknd-surprises-fans-by-dropping-two-new-songs/ |archive-date=December 4, 2020 | date=December 27, 2015 |website=[[CKIS-FM]]}}</ref> On April 23, he was featured on Beyoncé's sixth studio album ''[[Lemonade (Beyoncé album)|Lemonade]]'' on the track "[[6 Inch]]".<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 31, 2016 |title=Listen to The Weeknd and Belly's Demo Version of Beyoncé's "6 Inch" |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2016/10/the-weeknd-new-song-all-that-money-6-inch-demo-feat-belly |access-date=April 22, 2023 |work=Complex |archive-date=April 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422155236/https://www.complex.com/music/2016/10/the-weeknd-new-song-all-that-money-6-inch-demo-feat-belly |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 26, Tesfaye was featured on [[Cashmere Cat]]'s single "[[Wild Love (Cashmere Cat song)|Wild Love]]" with [[Francis and the Lights]], which served as the lead single from Cashmere Cat's debut studio album ''[[9 (Cashmere Cat album)|9]]'' (2017).<ref>{{Cite news|last=Morris|first=Jesse|date=August 24, 2016|title=It Sounds Like a Weeknd and Cashmere Cat Collab Is on the Way|website=[[Complex Networks]]|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2016/08/the-weeknd-previews-cashmere-cat-collaboration|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223932/https://www.complex.com/music/2016/08/the-weeknd-previews-cashmere-cat-collaboration|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref>

=== 2016–2019: ''Starboy'' and ''My Dear Melancholy'', ===
[[File:The Weeknd (253662129).jpeg|thumb|260x260px|Tesfaye performing at [[Lollapalooza Chile]] during the ''[[Starboy: Legend of the Fall Tour]]'' in 2017]]

In September 2016, Tesfaye announced that his third studio album, ''[[Starboy (album)|Starboy]]'', would be released on November 25, and included collaborations with now-disbanded French electronic music duo [[Daft Punk]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Mench|first=Chris|date=August 23, 2016|title=The Weeknd Is Reportedly Working with Daft Punk|website=[[Complex Networks]]|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2016/08/the-weeknd-working-with-daft-punk|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160824143608/http://www.complex.com/music/2016/08/the-weeknd-working-with-daft-punk|archive-date=August 24, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Pearce|first=Sheldon|date=September 21, 2016|title=The Weeknd Announces New Album Starboy|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/67755-the-weeknd-announces-new-album-starboy/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223937/https://pitchfork.com/news/67755-the-weeknd-announces-new-album-starboy/|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> He released the album's [[Starboy (song)|title track]], which featured the duo on September 21.<ref>{{Cite news|date=September 22, 2016|title=Hear the Weeknd's new track with Daft Punk, Starboy|website=[[The Guardian]]|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/sep/22/hear-the-weeknds-new-track-with-daft-punk-starboy|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301172411/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/sep/22/hear-the-weeknds-new-track-with-daft-punk-starboy|archive-date=March 1, 2021|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The song debuted at number 40 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, and peaked at number one, making it Tesfaye's third number-one single.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=January 20, 2021|title=The Weeknd's 'Starboy,' Featuring Daft Punk, Hits No. 1 on Hot 100 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7633336/hot-100-the-weeknd-starboy-daft-punk-hits-number-one|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120110659/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7633336/hot-100-the-weeknd-starboy-daft-punk-hits-number-one|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 20, 2021|access-date=September 28, 2021}}</ref> As of March 2023, the song is certified Diamond by the RIAA.<ref>{{Cite web|date=February 1, 2021|title=Gold & Platinum - RIAA|website=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=The+Weeknd&ti=Starboy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201081033/https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=The+Weeknd&ti=Starboy|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 1, 2021|access-date=September 28, 2021}}</ref> Their second collaboration, "[[I Feel It Coming]]" was released on November 24. The single peaked at number four on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Zwilling|first=Eric|date=September 21, 2016|title=Listen to Daft Punk's new collaboration with The Weeknd, 'Starboy'|url=https://dancingastronaut.com/2016/09/daft-punk-the-weeknd-collaboration-listen/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107130837/https://dancingastronaut.com/2016/09/daft-punk-the-weeknd-collaboration-listen/|archive-date=November 7, 2020|website=[[Dancing Astronaut]]}}</ref> On October 1, Tesfaye made a second appearance on ''Saturday Night Live'' as the musical guest alongside actress [[Margot Robbie]]. During the show, he performed "Starboy" and "[[False Alarm (The Weeknd song)|False Alarm]]".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Peters|first=Mitchell|date=October 2, 2016|title=Watch The Weeknd Perform 'Starboy' and 'False Alarm' on 'SNL' Season Premiere|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7526619/the-weeknd-perform-starboy-false-alarm-on-snl-saturday-night-live|access-date=May 25, 2021|archive-date=May 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210525140031/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7526619/the-weeknd-perform-starboy-false-alarm-on-snl-saturday-night-live|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 23, he released the short film ''M A N I A''. Directed by Grant Singer, it featured excerpts from the album, including snippets from "[[All I Know (The Weeknd song)|All I Know]]" featuring [[Future (rapper)|Future]], "[[Sidewalks (The Weeknd song)|Sidewalks]]" featuring [[Kendrick Lamar]], "[[Secrets (The Weeknd song)|Secrets]]" and "[[Die for You (The Weeknd song)|Die for You]]".<ref>{{Cite news|date=November 23, 2016|title=Watch The Weeknd's New Short Film Mania|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/69997-watch-the-weeknds-new-short-film-mania/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124093812/http://pitchfork.com/news/69997-watch-the-weeknds-new-short-film-mania/|archive-date=November 24, 2016}}</ref> Upon release, the album debuted at number one on the U.S. ''Billboard'' 200 with 348,000 units, making it Tesfaye's second consecutive number-one album.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=January 30, 2021|title=The Weeknd's 'Starboy' Bows at No. 1 on Billboard 200 With Third-Biggest Debut of 2016 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7597375/the-weeknd-starboy-billboard-200-no-1|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130022651/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7597375/the-weeknd-starboy-billboard-200-no-1|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 30, 2021|access-date=September 29, 2021}}</ref> As of January 2019, the album is certified [[RIAA certification|triple platinum]] by the RIAA.<ref>{{Cite web|date=February 1, 2021|title=Gold & Platinum - RIAA|website=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=The+Weeknd&ti=Starboy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201081033/https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=The+Weeknd&ti=Starboy|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 1, 2021|access-date=September 29, 2021}}</ref> The album won Best Urban Contemporary Album at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards]], making it Tesfaye's second win in the category.<ref>{{Cite news|date=January 28, 2018|title=NewsAlert: Starboy Wins Best Urban Contemporary Album for the Weeknd|work=[[National Post]]|agency=[[The Canadian Press]]|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/entertainment-pmn/newsalert-starboy-wins-best-urban-contemporary-album-for-the-weeknd|access-date=April 16, 2019|archive-date=January 7, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223930/https://nationalpost.com/pmn/entertainment-pmn/newsalert-starboy-wins-best-urban-contemporary-album-for-the-weeknd|url-status=live}}</ref>

On February 17, 2017, the Weeknd began his fifth concert tour, called [[Starboy: Legend of the Fall Tour]]. The tour was in support of his third studio album [[Starboy (album)|Starboy]] (2016) and concluded on December 14, 2017. He visited the continents Europa, North- and South America and Oceania. On February 15, 2017, Tesfaye was featured on [[Nav (rapper)|Nav]]'s commercial debut single "[[Some Way]]", which also served as the lead single from his [[Nav (mixtape)|self-titled mixtape]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Blistein|first=John|date=February 16, 2017|title=Hear the Weeknd's Sultry 'Some Way' Collaboration With Nav|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-the-weeknds-sultry-some-way-collaboration-with-nav-w467422|url-status=live|url-access=limited|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223934/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/hear-the-weeknds-sultry-some-way-collaboration-with-nav-192851/|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> On February 24, he appeared on Future's sixth studio album ''[[Hndrxx]]'', on the song "[[Comin Out Strong]]".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Brandle|first=Lars|date=February 24, 2017|title=Future Releases New Album 'HNDRXX' Featuring The Weeknd and Rihanna: Listen|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7701959/future-album-hndrxx-the-weeknd-rihanna|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223936/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7701959/future-album-hndrxx-the-weeknd-rihanna|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> On April 19, Tesfaye appeared on the [[Lust for Life (Lana Del Rey song)|title track]] and second single from [[Lana Del Rey]]'s [[Lust for Life (Lana Del Rey album)|fifth studio album]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Gaca|first=Anna|date=April 19, 2017|title=For Better or Worse, Lana Del Rey and the Weeknd's "Lust for Life" Is a Lana Del Rey Song|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|url=https://www.spin.com/2017/04/lana-del-rey-lust-for-life-song-review/|access-date=May 25, 2021|archive-date=May 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210525034720/https://www.spin.com/2017/04/lana-del-rey-lust-for-life-song-review/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Pearce|first=Sheldon|date=April 20, 2017|title=Lana Del Rey "Lust for Life" ft. The Weeknd|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/19012-lana-del-rey-lust-for-life-ft-the-weeknd/|access-date=May 25, 2021|archive-date=April 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422103239/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/19012-lana-del-rey-lust-for-life-ft-the-weeknd/|url-status=live}}</ref> On August 15, he was featured on [[French Montana]]'s track "[[A Lie]]", the third single from his second studio album ''[[Jungle Rules]]''. He then appeared on the [[Virgil Abloh]]-directed music video for [[Lil Uzi Vert]]'s "[[XO Tour Llif3]]" alongside Nav. He was later featured on Lil Uzi Vert's debut album ''[[Luv Is Rage 2]]'' on the track "UnFazed" and on [[Gucci Mane]]'s eleventh studio album ''[[Mr. Davis]]'' on the track "[[Curve (song)|Curve]]".[[File:The Weeknd with hand in the air performing live in Hong Kong in November 2018 (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|269x269px|Tesfaye performing in Hong Kong in November 2018]]
On February 2, 2018, Tesfaye contributed to the [[Black Panther (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'' on the song "[[Pray for Me (The Weeknd and Kendrick Lamar song)|Pray for Me]]" with Kendrick Lamar. The track served as the third single from the soundtrack, and peaked at number seven on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Boykins|first=Austin|date=January 31, 2018|title=TDE Reveals Loaded Tracklist for 'Black Panther' Soundtrack|website=Hypebeast|url=https://hypebeast.com/2018/1/tde-black-panther-soundtrack-cover-tracklist|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223936/https://hypebeast.com/2018/1/tde-black-panther-soundtrack-cover-tracklist|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Kendrick Lamar And The Weeknd Team Up For 'Pray For Me'|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/allsongs/2018/02/02/582641529/kendrick-lamar-and-the-weeknd-team-up-for-pray-for-me|access-date=August 15, 2021|website=NPR.org|date=February 2, 2018|language=en|last1=Madden|first1=Sidney|archive-date=February 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180202160608/https://www.npr.org/sections/allsongs/2018/02/02/582641529/kendrick-lamar-and-the-weeknd-team-up-for-pray-for-me|url-status=live}}</ref>

On March 30, 2018, Tesfaye released his debut [[extended play]] ''[[My Dear Melancholy]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sargent|first=Jordan|date=March 29, 2018|title=The Weekend Announces New Album 'My Dear Melancholy,'|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/03/the-weeknd-new-album-my-dear-melancholy-announcement/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223941/https://www.spin.com/2018/03/the-weeknd-new-album-my-dear-melancholy-announcement/|archive-date=January 7, 2021|website=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=March 27, 2018|title=Is The Weeknd Dropping A New Album This Week?|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/03/the-weeknd-dropping-album-rumor-report/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223937/https://www.vibe.com/2018/03/the-weeknd-dropping-album-rumor-report|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> after news of the project were teased and leaked.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Murray|first=Robin|date=March 29, 2018|title=Has Someone Accidentally Leaked News of the Weeknd's New Album?|work=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|url=https://clashmusic.com/news/has-someone-accidentally-leaked-news-of-the-weeknds-new-album|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223940/https://clashmusic.com/news/has-someone-accidentally-leaked-news-of-the-weeknds-new-album|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Lamarre|first=Carl|date=March 27, 2018|title=Is The Weeknd Dropping a New Album on Friday?|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8263214/the-weeknd-new-album-instagram|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223915/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8263214/the-weeknd-new-album-instagram|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> The EP debuted at number one on the ''Billboard'' 200 with 169,000 units, making it Tesfaye's third consecutive number-one album and the shortest album, by track count, to top the chart in eight years.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=November 9, 2020|title=The Weeknd Scores Third Consecutive No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'My Dear Melancholy'|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8298065/the-weeknd-no-1-album-billboard-200-my-dear-melancholy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109025806/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8298065/the-weeknd-no-1-album-billboard-200-my-dear-melancholy|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 9, 2020|access-date=September 29, 2021}}</ref> On April 6, Tesfaye released the EP's lead single "[[Call Out My Name]]", which peaked at number four on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{Cite news|date=March 28, 2018|title=The Weeknd teases new song release|work=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]]|url=https://www.iol.co.za/entertainment/music/international/the-weeknd-teases-new-song-release-14133016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223934/https://www.iol.co.za/entertainment/music/international/the-weeknd-teases-new-song-release-14133016|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Goddard|first=Kevin|date=March 29, 2018|title=Stream The Weeknd's "My Dear Melancholy" EP|work=HotNewHipHop|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/stream-the-weeknds-my-dear-melancholy-ep-news.46817.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223940/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/stream-the-weeknds-my-dear-melancholy-ep-news.46817.html|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> On April 13, he headlined the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] for the first time.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Unterberger |first=Andrew |date=April 14, 2018 |title=The Weeknd Fulfills His Coachella Destiny With Triumphant Headlining Set |url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/events/weeknd-coachella-2018-day-one-recap-8318723/ |access-date=April 20, 2022 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=April 20, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420032630/https://www.billboard.com/culture/events/weeknd-coachella-2018-day-one-recap-8318723/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Blistein |first=Jon |date=January 3, 2018 |title=Beyonce, Eminem, the Weeknd to Headline Coachella 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/beyonce-eminem-the-weeknd-to-headline-coachella-2018-201999/ |access-date=April 20, 2022 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=April 20, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420032453/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/beyonce-eminem-the-weeknd-to-headline-coachella-2018-201999/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He appeared in multiple festivals throughout 2018 to support the EP, most notably the [[Mawazine]] Festival in Morocco,<ref>{{cite news|last=Senoussi|first=Zoubida|url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/06/249735/mawazine-2018-friday-night-fever-with-starboy-the-weeknd-at-olm-souissi|title=Mawazine 2018: Friday Night Fever with 'Starboy' The Weeknd at OLM Souissi|work=[[Morocco World News]]|date=June 30, 2018|access-date=February 20, 2024|archive-date=February 20, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240220200411/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/06/249735/mawazine-2018-friday-night-fever-with-starboy-the-weeknd-at-olm-souissi|url-status=live}}</ref> Lollapalooza in both Chicago and Berlin,<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/lollapalooza-2018-the-weeknd-dua-lipa-carly-rae-jepsen-highlight-day-three-706709/|title=Lollapalooza 2018: The Weeknd, Dua Lipa, Carly Rae Jepsen Highlight Day Three|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=August 5, 2018|access-date=February 20, 2024|archive-date=February 20, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240220200410/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/lollapalooza-2018-the-weeknd-dua-lipa-carly-rae-jepsen-highlight-day-three-706709/|url-status=live}}</ref> and a post-race concert at the [[Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Engelman|first=Nicole|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/the-weeknd-bella-hadid-abu-dhabi-trip-8486438/|title=The Weeknd and Bella Hadid Take a PDA-Filled Trip to Abu Dhabi|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 26, 2018|access-date=February 20, 2024|archive-date=February 20, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240220200410/https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/the-weeknd-bella-hadid-abu-dhabi-trip-8486438/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On June 6, 2018, Tesfaye announced his new [[Apple Music 1]] radio show ''[[Memento Mori (radio show)|Memento Mori]]''. The first episode was released two days later.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Penrose|first=Nerisha|date=June 6, 2018|title=The Weeknd Announces New Beats 1 Radio Show Memento Mori|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8459680/the-weeknd-memento-mori-beats-one-radio-show|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223921/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8459680/the-weeknd-memento-mori-beats-one-radio-show|archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> He would later feature on two tracks from Travis Scott's third studio album, [[Astroworld (album)|''Astroworld'']], which were "Skeletons" and "[[Wake Up (Travis Scott song)|Wake Up]]" on August 3, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 31, 2018 |title=Here are the full album credits for Travis Scott's ASTROWORLD |url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/08/03/travis-scott-astroworld-credits |access-date=January 1, 2024 |website=The FADER |language=en |archive-date=March 2, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302204615/https://www.thefader.com/2018/08/03/travis-scott-astroworld-credits |url-status=live }}</ref> On November 21, he released his first [[greatest hits album]] ''[[The Weeknd in Japan]].''<ref>{{Cite web|title=ザ・ウィークエンド・イン・ジャパン（シングルス・コレクション|trans-title=The Weeknd in Japan (Singles Collection)|url=https://www.universal-music.co.jp/the-weeknd/products/uicu-1305/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020154836/https://www.universal-music.co.jp/the-weeknd/products/uicu-1305/|archive-date=October 20, 2019|publisher=[[Universal Music Group]]|language=ja}}</ref> In support of the album and his EP [[My Dear Melancholy]], he began his sixth concert tour, [[the Weeknd Asia Tour]], a six-show tour of Asia during November and December. On January 11, 2019, Tesfaye was featured on [[Gesaffelstein]]'s song "[[Lost in the Fire]]", the second single from his second studio album ''[[Hyperion (Gesaffelstein album)|Hyperion]].''<ref>{{Cite news |last=Blais-Billie |first=Braudie |date=January 11, 2019 |title=Listen to Gesaffelstein and the Weeknd's New Song "Lost in the Fire" |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-gesaffelstein-and-the-weeknds-new-song-lost-in-fire/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223939/https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-gesaffelstein-and-the-weeknds-new-song-lost-in-fire/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021}}</ref> On April 18, he released "[[Power Is Power]]" with [[SZA (singer)|SZA]] and Travis Scott, the lead single from the ''[[Game of Thrones]]''-inspired [[For the Throne: Music Inspired by the HBO Series Game of Thrones|soundtrack]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pearce |first=Sheldon |date=April 18, 2019 |title=SZA / The Weeknd / Travis Scott 'Power Is Power' |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/sza-the-weeknd-travis-scott-power-is-power/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419144546/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/sza-the-weeknd-travis-scott-power-is-power/ |archive-date=April 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.billboard.com/video/bbnews050619sza-8510131 |title=SZA, The Weeknd and Travis Scott Share Video For 'Game of Thrones' Inspired Track |date=May 5, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223921/https://www.billboard.com/video/bbnews050619sza-8510131 |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |url-status=live |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>

=== 2019–2021: ''After Hours'' ===
On November 24, 2019, Tesfaye teased his single "[[Blinding Lights]]" through a [[Mercedes-Benz]] commercial.<ref>{{Cite news |date=November 24, 2019 |title=The Weeknd to Release New Single 'Blinding Lights' on Black Friday |work=[[Rap-Up]] |url=https://www.rap-up.com/2019/11/24/the-weeknd-new-single-blinding-lights/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128132032/https://www.rap-up.com/2019/11/24/the-weeknd-new-single-blinding-lights/ |archive-date=November 28, 2019}}</ref> On November 27, he released "[[Heartless (The Weeknd song)|Heartless]]" as the lead single from his fourth studio album. The song debuted at number thirty-two on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and peaked at number one, making it Tesfaye's fourth number-one single.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Five Burning Questions: Billboard Staffers Discuss The Weeknd's Top 40 Debut For 'Heartless' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545288/the-weeknd-heartless-five-burning-questions |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319225809/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545288/the-weeknd-heartless-five-burning-questions |archive-date=March 19, 2020 | date=December 3, 2019 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Trust |first=Gary |title=The Weeknd's 'Heartless' Hits No. 1 on Hot 100, Mariah Carey's 'All I Want for Christmas Is You' Returns to No. 3 High |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545778/the-weeknd-heartless-no-1-hot-100 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200116053415/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545778/the-weeknd-heartless-no-1-hot-100 |archive-date=January 16, 2020 |date=December 9, 2019 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> "Blinding Lights" was released two days after the release of "Heartless" on November 29. The single debuted at number eleven on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and peaked at number one, making it Tesfaye's fifth number-one single.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |title=The Weeknd's 'Blinding Lights' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Doja Cat's 'Say So' Enters Top 10 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9346375/weeknd-blinding-lights-number-one-hot-100 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331195920/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9346375/weeknd-blinding-lights-number-one-hot-100 |archive-date=March 31, 2020 |date=March 30, 2020 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> "Blinding Lights" would then go on to become the first song in the chart's history to hold a spot in the top ten for an entire year.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=March 9, 2021|title=The Weeknd Talks Unprecedented Year in Hot 100's Top 10 With 'Blinding Lights': 'This Is Truly a Result of the Fans'|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-chart-record-reaction/|access-date=November 26, 2021|magazine=Billboard|language=en-US|archive-date=November 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211126174840/https://www.billboard.com/pro/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-chart-record-reaction/|url-status=live}}</ref> It also became the [[List of Billboard Hot 100 chart achievements and milestones|longest charting song by a solo artist on the Hot 100]] at 90 weeks, ending the week of September 11, 2021.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=August 16, 2021|title=The Weeknd's 'Blinding Lights' Spends Record-Breaking 88th Week on Billboard Hot 100|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-hot-100-record-88-weeks/|access-date=November 26, 2021|magazine=Billboard|language=en-US|archive-date=November 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211126174838/https://www.billboard.com/pro/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-hot-100-record-88-weeks/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=The Weeknd's "Blinding Lights" Is Now the Longest-Charting Billboard Hot 100 Song of All Time|url=https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-longest-charting-song-billboard-hot-100|access-date=September 29, 2021|website=Complex|language=en|archive-date=September 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210929152346/https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-longest-charting-song-billboard-hot-100|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 23, 2021, "Blinding Lights" was ranked as the #1 Greatest Hot 100 Hit of All Time by ''Billboard'', surpassing "[[The Twist (song)|The Twist]]" by [[Chubby Checker]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Mamo|first=Heran|date=November 23, 2021|title=The Greatest Hit: The New No. 1 Song of All Time|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/features/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-billboard-cover-story-2021-interview-1235001282/|access-date=November 26, 2021|magazine=Billboard|language=en-US|archive-date=December 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211202115058/https://www.billboard.com/music/features/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-billboard-cover-story-2021-interview-1235001282/|url-status=live}}</ref> On January 1, 2023, it became the most streamed song on Spotify with 3.3 billion streams.<ref>{{Citation |title=The Weeknd's 'Blinding Lights' becomes the most-streamed song on Spotify |date=January 4, 2023 |url=https://www.cbc.ca/music/the-weeknd-s-blinding-lights-becomes-the-most-streamed-song-on-spotify-1.6704361 |language=en |access-date=January 31, 2023 |archive-date=January 31, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131185916/https://www.cbc.ca/music/the-weeknd-s-blinding-lights-becomes-the-most-streamed-song-on-spotify-1.6704361 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On February 19, 2020, Tesfaye revealed that his fourth studio album would be titled ''[[After Hours (The Weeknd album)|After Hours]]'', and would be released on March 20. He also released the album's [[After Hours (The Weeknd song)|title track]] as a promotional single.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Brandle |first=Lars |date=February 19, 2020 |title=The Weeknd Sets 'After Hours' Release Date, Shares Dark Title Track: Listen |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8551359/the-weeknd-after-hours-release-date-title-track-release |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313135747/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8551359/the-weeknd-after-hours-release-date-title-track-release |archive-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> On March 7, he made his third appearance as a musical guest on ''Saturday Night Live'', alongside actor [[Daniel Craig]]. On the show, he performed "Blinding Lights" and debuted the track "[[Scared to Live]]".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Young |first=Alex |date=March 8, 2020 |title=The Weeknd Debuts New Song, Appears in Sketch on SNL |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/the-weeknd-snl-video/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320035057/https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/the-weeknd-snl-video/ |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |website=[[Consequence (publication)|Consequence]]}}</ref> Tesfaye released the album's third single "[[In Your Eyes (The Weeknd song)|In Your Eyes]]" on March 24. The track peaked at number sixteen on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{Cite web|date=November 27, 2020|title=The Weeknd Loses His Head in Gory New "In Your Eyes" Video |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-loses-his-head-in-gory-new-in-your-eyes-video/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127021729/https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-loses-his-head-in-gory-new-in-your-eyes-video/|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 27, 2020|access-date=September 29, 2021}}</ref>

Upon release,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Strauss |first=Matthew |title=Listen to the Weeknd's New Album After Hours |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-the-weeknds-new-album-after-hours/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320145830/https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-the-weeknds-new-album-after-hours/ |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |date=March 20, 2020 |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref> ''After Hours'' debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200, earning 444,000 units, marking Tesfaye's fourth consecutive number-one album.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |title=The Weeknd's 'After Hours' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart With Biggest Week of 2020 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9345850/the-weeknd-after-hours-billboard-200-debut-2020-biggest-week |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329225706/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9345850/the-weeknd-after-hours-billboard-200-debut-2020-biggest-week |archive-date=March 29, 2020 |date=March 29, 2020 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> It became the most streamed R&B album of all time, surpassing Tesfaye's own ''Starboy''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=THE WEEKND CAPTURES #1 ALBUM AND #1 ON BILLBOARD HOT 100 WITH AFTER HOURS AND BLINDING LIGHTS|url=https://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/the-weeknd-captures-1-album-and-1-on-billboard-hot-100-with-after-hours-and-blinding-lights/|access-date=November 26, 2021|website=Umusic|language=en-US|archive-date=November 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211126192241/https://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/the-weeknd-captures-1-album-and-1-on-billboard-hot-100-with-after-hours-and-blinding-lights/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="McIntyre">{{Cite web|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|title=The Weeknd Scores The Largest Streaming Week Ever For An R&B Album|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2020/04/02/the-weeknd-scores-the-largest-streaming-week-ever-for-an-rb-album/|access-date=November 26, 2021|website=Forbes|language=en|archive-date=November 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211126192238/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2020/04/02/the-weeknd-scores-the-largest-streaming-week-ever-for-an-rb-album/|url-status=live}}</ref> In the album's first charting week, Tesfaye also became the first artist to lead the ''Billboard'' 200, ''Billboard'' Hot 100, [[Artist 100|''Billboard'' Artist 100]], Hot 100 Songwriters and Hot 100 Producers charts simultaneously, and repeated his lead the following week.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Trust |first=Gary |title=The Weeknd on Being the First Artist to Top These 5 Charts at Once: 'It Feels Like a Huge Blessing' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9348979/the-weeknd-interview-historic-chart-domination-exclusive |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223939/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9348979/the-weeknd-interview-historic-chart-domination-exclusive |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |date=April 1, 2020 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd also repeats at No. 1 on the Billboard 200, Hot 100 & Artist 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9353926/the-weeknd-songwriters-chart-30roc-producers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223925/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9353926/the-weeknd-songwriters-chart-30roc-producers |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Xander | last=Zellner | date=April 8, 2020 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> The deluxe version of ''After Hours'' was released on March 29, 2020, and contained the tracks "Nothing Compares", "Missed You" and "Final Lullaby".<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=March 30, 2020 |title=The Weeknd Adds Three New Songs to 'After Hours' Deluxe Edition |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-new-songs-after-hours-deluxe-edition-974989/ |access-date=April 22, 2023 |magazine=Rolling Stone |archive-date=April 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422155237/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-new-songs-after-hours-deluxe-edition-974989/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On August 7, 2020, Tesfaye was featured on the late [[Juice Wrld]]'s single "[[Smile (Juice Wrld and the Weeknd song)|Smile]]" from his first posthumous album ''[[Legends Never Die (Juice Wrld album)|Legends Never Die]]''. On August 28, he was featured on [[Calvin Harris]]' single "[[Over Now (Calvin Harris and the Weeknd song)|Over Now]]". On October 30, Tesfaye appeared on Ariana Grande's song "[[Off the Table]]" from her sixth studio album ''[[Positions (album)|Positions]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Ariana Grande And The Weeknd's 'Off The Table' Lyrics Are About Her Finding Love After Losing Mac Miller |url=https://www.elle.com/culture/music/a34532474/ariana-grande-the-weeknd-off-the-table-lyrics-meaning-mac-miller/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223926/https://www.elle.com/culture/music/a34532474/ariana-grande-the-weeknd-off-the-table-lyrics-meaning-mac-miller/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=ALYSSA | last=BAILEY | date=October 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Ariana Grande Unveils 'Positions' Track List |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9472449/ariana-grande-positions-track-list/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024235455/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9472449/ariana-grande-positions-track-list/ |archive-date=October 24, 2020 | first=Ashley | last=Iasimone | date=October 24, 2020 | magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> On the same day, he appeared on [[Oneohtrix Point Never]]'s track "No Nightmares" from his ninth studio album ''[[Magic Oneohtrix Point Never]]'', which he also executive produced with OPN.<ref>{{Cite news |title=The Weeknd Joins Oneohtrix Point Never on New Song 'No Nightmares' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/oneohtrix-point-never-the-weeknd-new-song-no-nightmares-1081251/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223954/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/oneohtrix-point-never-the-weeknd-new-song-no-nightmares-1081251/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |date=October 26, 2020 | url-access=limited | magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref> On November 5, he appeared on the remix of [[Maluma]]'s "[[Hawái (song)|Hawái]]", was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Urban Fusion/Performance|Best Urban Fusion/Performance]] at the [[22nd Annual Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news | title=The Weeknd Sings in Spanglish on Fiery 'Hawái' Remix With Maluma: Watch the Video |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/9478647/maluma-the-weeknd-hawai-remix-video/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223938/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/9478647/maluma-the-weeknd-hawai-remix-video/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Jessica | last=Roiz | date=November 5, 2020 | magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 Latin Grammy nominations: Bad Bunny, Maluma, and more|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/2021-latin-grammy-nominations-bad-133000922.html|access-date=September 29, 2021|website=www.yahoo.com|date=September 28, 2021|language=en-US|archive-date=September 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210929152346/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/2021-latin-grammy-nominations-bad-133000922.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 10, he performed at [[iHeartRadio]]'s [[Jingle Ball]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Harry Styles, Billie Eilish, Shawn Mendes to Perform at Virtual iHeartRadio Jingle Ball |url=https://people.com/music/virtual-iheartradio-jingle-ball-2020-performers/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223952/https://people.com/music/virtual-iheartradio-jingle-ball-2020-performers/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 | first=Georgia | last=Slater | date=October 30, 2020 | website=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> On February 5, 2021, Tesfaye released his second greatest hits album ''[[The Highlights]]''. The album debuted at number two on the US ''Billboard'' 200, making it Tesfaye's highest charting compilation album and the biggest first week debut for a greatest hits album since ''[[Fully Loaded: God's Country]]'' (2019).<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=February 14, 2021 |title=Morgan Wallen's 'Dangerous' No. 1 for Fifth Week on Billboard 200 While 'If I Know Me' Hits Top 10 for First Time |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9526109/morgan-wallen-dangerous-tops-billboard-200-for-fifth-week/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415045949/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9526109/morgan-wallen-dangerous-tops-billboard-200-for-fifth-week/ |archive-date=April 15, 2021 |access-date=July 14, 2021 |magazine=Billboard |language=en}}</ref>[[File:Raymond James Stadium (50898195996).jpg|thumb|Tesfaye headlined the [[Super Bowl LV halftime show]] at the [[Raymond James Stadium]] in 2021]]Tesfaye headlined the [[Super Bowl LV halftime show]] on February 7, 2021, becoming the first Canadian solo artist to headline the show.<ref>{{Cite news |last=McCarriston |first=Shanna |date=November 12, 2020 |title=Super Bowl LV: The Weeknd announced as Pepsi Halftime Show performer |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/super-bowl-lv-the-weeknd-announced-as-pepsi-halftime-show-performer/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107224001/https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/super-bowl-lv-the-weeknd-announced-as-pepsi-halftime-show-performer/ |archive-date=January 7, 2021 |website=[[CBSSports.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=O'Connor |first1=Roisin |last2=Michallon |first2=Clémence |date=February 8, 2021 |title=Super Bowl halftime show live: The Weeknd performs with dancers in face bandages at 2021 game |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/super-bowl-halftime-show-the-weeknd-live-b1798883.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208011804/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/super-bowl-halftime-show-the-weeknd-live-b1798883.html |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |website=[[The Independent]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Steussy |first1=Lauren |last2=DeNinno |first2=Nadine |date=February 8, 2021 |title=What happened to The Weeknd's face at Super Bowl 2021 halftime show? |url=https://nypost.com/2021/02/07/what-happened-to-the-weeknds-face-at-super-bowl-2021-halftime-show/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208014344/https://nypost.com/2021/02/07/what-happened-to-the-weeknds-face-at-super-bowl-2021-halftime-show/ |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |website=[[New York Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=February 7, 2021 |title=Best of The Weeknd and the Super Bowl 55 halftime show |url=https://www.usatoday.com/picture-gallery/sports/nfl/super-bowl/2021/02/08/best-photos-super-bowl-5-halftime-show-the-weeknd/4430380001/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209021700/https://www.usatoday.com/picture-gallery/sports/nfl/super-bowl/2021/02/08/best-photos-super-bowl-5-halftime-show-the-weeknd/4430380001/ |archive-date=February 9, 2021 |website=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> He reportedly spent US$7 million of his own money on the Super Bowl performance.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Bain |first=Katie |date=January 28, 2021 |title=The Weeknd on the Crew That Boosted Him From 'Basically Homeless' to the Super Bowl |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/9516909/the-weeknd-xo-records-billboard-cover-story-interview-2021 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128235510/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/9516909/the-weeknd-xo-records-billboard-cover-story-interview-2021/ |archive-date=January 28, 2021 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> Reviews of the performance were generally positive.<ref name="Caramanica">{{Cite news |last=Caramanica |first=Jon |author-link=Jon Caramanica |date=February 8, 2021 |title=The Weeknd Emerges From the Shadows at the Super Bowl Halftime Show |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/07/arts/music/the-weeknd-super-bowl-halftime-review.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208015941/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/07/arts/music/the-weeknd-super-bowl-halftime-review.html |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=February 8, 2021 |title=Super Bowl halftime show review: The Weeknd wasn't great (but it's not all his fault) |url=https://ftw.usatoday.com/2021/02/super-bowl-halftime-show-weeknd-review |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208015211/https://ftw.usatoday.com/2021/02/super-bowl-halftime-show-weeknd-review |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |website=[[USA Today]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Kornhaber |first=Spencer |date=February 8, 2021 |title=The First Super Bowl Halftime Show About the Depravity of Halftime Shows |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/culture/archive/2021/02/the-cynical-fun-of-the-weeknds-halftime-show/617960/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210210113958/https://www.theatlantic.com/culture/archive/2021/02/the-cynical-fun-of-the-weeknds-halftime-show/617960/ |archive-date=February 10, 2021 |website=[[The Atlantic]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Patten |first=Dominic |date=February 8, 2021 |title=The Weeknd's Super Bowl Halftime Show Scores A Touchdown With A Technical Spectacle & Mixtape Of Hits – Review |url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/weeknd-super-bowl-halftime-show-review-nfl-cbs-1234689348/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208015623/https://deadline.com/2021/02/weeknd-super-bowl-halftime-show-review-nfl-cbs-1234689348/ |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Julious |first=Britt |date=February 7, 2021 |title=Review: The Weeknd's Super Bowl halftime performance was an expensive nothing |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/sc-ent-super-bowl-halftime-review-0207-20210208-ie2smv3xwbg45l6vqxc4zrhlp4-story.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208025139/https://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/sc-ent-super-bowl-halftime-review-0207-20210208-ie2smv3xwbg45l6vqxc4zrhlp4-story.html |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |website=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Fekau |first=Mesfin |date=February 7, 2021 |title=Review: Yawn, is it Monday yet? The Weeknd bores at halftime |url=https://apnews.com/article/nfl-new-york-super-bowl-her-football-f375de5012d0dcaa454462d4c8752c16 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208004138/https://apnews.com/article/nfl-new-york-super-bowl-her-football-f375de5012d0dcaa454462d4c8752c16 |archive-date=February 8, 2021 |work=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref> The show resulted in a surge in streaming and downloads for Tesfaye's ''After Hours'' album as well as for the seven other songs he performed.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=February 11, 2021 |title=The Weeknd's Streams Increase 41% After Super Bowl Halftime Show |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9524744/the-weeknd-streams-increase-super-bowl-halftime-show |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211073241/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9524744/the-weeknd-streams-increase-super-bowl-halftime-show/ |archive-date=February 11, 2021 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=February 9, 2021 |title=The Weeknd's Sales Up 385% After Super Bowl Halftime Show |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9523400/the-weeknd-sales-super-bowl-halftime-show/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209233740/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9523400/the-weeknd-sales-super-bowl-halftime-show/ |archive-date=February 9, 2021 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> The halftime show earned three nominations at the [[73rd Primetime Emmy Awards]]: [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Variety Special (Live)|Outstanding Variety Special (Live)]], [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lighting Design / Lighting Direction for a Variety Special|Outstanding Lighting Design/Lighting Direction for a Variety Special]], and [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Technical Direction, Camerawork, Video Control for a Limited Series, Movie, or Special|Outstanding Technical Direction, Camerawork, Video Control for a Special]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Libbey |first=Peter |date=July 13, 2021 |title=Emmys 2021: The List of Nominees |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/13/arts/television/emmys-nominees-list-2021.html |url-access=limited |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20211228/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/13/arts/television/emmys-nominees-list-2021.html |archive-date=December 28, 2021 |access-date=July 14, 2021 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

Over 2021, Tesfaye reissued his three mixtapes in its authentic form with the original mixes and samples to celebrate the tenth anniversary of their release, with ''House of Balloons'' coming first in March 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kiefer |first=Halle |date=March 21, 2021 |title=Step Inside the Weeknd's House of Balloons, Reissued for Its 10th Anniversary |url=https://www.vulture.com/2021/03/the-weeknds-house-of-balloons-reissued-for-10th-anniversary.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161009/https://www.vulture.com/2021/03/the-weeknds-house-of-balloons-reissued-for-10th-anniversary.html |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |access-date=August 3, 2021 |website=Vulture |language=en-us}}</ref> ''[[Thursday (album)|Thursday]]'''s reissue followed in August 2021,<ref>{{Cite web |date=August 18, 2021 |title=The Weeknd Shares Original Version of 'Thursday' Mixtape and MR. Capsule Collection for Its Tenth Anniversary |url=https://hypebeast.com/2021/8/the-weekend-thursday-mixtape-listen |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210830204325/https://hypebeast.com/2021/8/the-weekend-thursday-mixtape-listen |archive-date=August 30, 2021 |access-date=August 30, 2021 |website=HYPEBEAST}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=The Weeknd and MR. Team Up for Capsule Collection to Commemorate 'Thursday (Original)' Streaming Release |url=https://www.complex.com/style/the-weeknd-mr-capsule-collection-thursday-original-streaming-release/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210830204327/https://www.complex.com/style/the-weeknd-mr-capsule-collection-thursday-original-streaming-release/ |archive-date=August 30, 2021 |access-date=August 30, 2021 |website=Complex |language=en}}</ref> and in December, ''[[Echoes of Silence]]'' was reissued.<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Weeknd shares new "Echoes of Silence" video |url=https://www.thefader.com/2021/12/21/the-weeknd-echoes-of-silence-video |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161017/https://platform.twitter.com/widgets/widget_iframe.d37472b4a6622d0b1fff46ad904f6896.html?origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thefader.com |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |access-date=December 21, 2021 |website=The FADER |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=The Weeknd Celebrates 10-Year Anniversary of 'Echoes of Silence' by Sharing Title-Track Video |url=https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-new-echoes-of-silence-video-anniversary |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221170308/https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-new-echoes-of-silence-video-anniversary |archive-date=December 21, 2021 |access-date=December 21, 2021 |website=Complex |language=en}}</ref>

On April 23, Tesfaye released a remix of "[[Save Your Tears#Ariana Grande remix|Save Your Tears]]" with Ariana Grande, marking their third collaboration.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mamo |first=Heran |date=April 23, 2021 |title=The Weeknd Drops 'Save Your Tears' Remix With Ariana Grande: Stream It Now |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/the-weeknd-ariana-grande-save-your-tears-remix-stream-9561503/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221215181340/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/the-weeknd-ariana-grande-save-your-tears-remix-stream-9561503/ |archive-date=December 15, 2022 |access-date=January 7, 2024 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> The remix launched the song to the top of the Billboard Hot 100 on the chart dated May 8, 2021, becoming both artists' sixth number one hit.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Blanchet |first=Brenton |title=The Weeknd and Ariana Grande Score No. 1 Hit for "Save Your Tears" |url=https://www.complex.com/music/a/b-blanchet/the-weeknd-ariana-grande-no-1-hit-save-your-tears |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107111437/https://www.complex.com/music/a/b-blanchet/the-weeknd-ariana-grande-no-1-hit-save-your-tears |archive-date=January 7, 2024 |access-date=January 7, 2024 |website=Complex |language=en-us}}</ref> He later began to tease new music in the same month. When asked about a new album during an interview with ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', he explained that "if the last record is the ''After Hours'' of the night, then ''The Dawn'' is coming".<ref>{{cite web |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=May 4, 2021 |title=The Weeknd Drops Hints About 'Beautiful' New Music: 'The Dawn Is Coming' |url=https://www.variety.com/2021/music/news/the-weeknd-hints-new-music-the-dawn-1234965810/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602214620/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/the-weeknd-hints-new-music-the-dawn-1234965810/ |archive-date=June 2, 2021 |access-date=June 1, 2021 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> On May 11, Tesfaye performed "Save Your Tears" at the [[2021 Brit Awards|Brit Awards]]. He also accepted his first Brit Award for [[Brit Award for International Male Solo Artist|International Male Solo Artist]], which was presented to him by former [[First Lady of the United States|first lady of the United States]] [[Michelle Obama]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=May 11, 2021 |title=The Weeknd Brings Rainy 'Save Your Tears' to 2021 Brit Awards: Watch |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/9570807/the-weeknd-save-your-tears-brit-awards/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210622233536/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/9570807/the-weeknd-save-your-tears-brit-awards/ |archive-date=June 22, 2021 |access-date=June 30, 2021 |magazine=Billboard |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Beaumont-Thomas |first=Ben |date=May 11, 2021 |title=Brit awards 2021: the ceremony as it happened, with Dua Lipa, Taylor Swift and more |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/live/2021/may/11/brit-awards-2021-follow-it-live |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629124919/https://www.theguardian.com/music/live/2021/may/11/brit-awards-2021-follow-it-live |archive-date=June 29, 2021 |access-date=June 30, 2021 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On May 24, Tesfaye performed "Save Your Tears" at the [[2021 Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]]. He was nominated for a record sixteen awards, and won ten, including [[Billboard Music Award for Top Artist|Top Artist]] and [[Billboard Music Award for Top Hot 100 Song|Top Hot 100 Song]]. When accepting his awards, Tesfaye continued to tease new music by saying "the ''After Hours'' are done, and ''The Dawn'' is coming".<ref name="Cryptic">{{cite web |last=Singh |first=Ashish |date=May 28, 2021 |title=Is The Weeknd dropping an album? Fans say 'dawn is coming' after cryptic post |url=https://meaww.com/amp/the-weeknd-announce-new-album-the-dawn-is-coming-new-tweet-latest-new-billboard-awards-after-hours |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161004/https://meaww.com/the-weeknd-announce-new-album-the-dawn-is-coming-new-tweet-latest-new-billboard-awards-after-hours |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |access-date=June 1, 2021 |work=Meaww.com}}</ref> On May 28, he performed the remix of "Save Your Tears" at the [[2021 iHeartRadio Music Awards|iHeartRadio Music Awards]] with Ariana Grande. On June 25, Tesfaye appeared on [[Doja Cat]]'s single "[[You Right]]" from her third studio album ''[[Planet Her]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Park |first=Sabrina |date=June 25, 2021 |title=Doja Cat and The Weeknd Take Us to Another Universe in Their "You Right" Music Video |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a36843818/doja-cat-you-right-the-weeknd-video-lyrics/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211009141039/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a36843818/doja-cat-you-right-the-weeknd-video-lyrics/ |archive-date=October 9, 2021 |access-date=September 29, 2021 |magazine=Harper's BAZAAR |language=en-US}}</ref> On July 22, he appeared on Belly's single "[[Better Believe]]" with [[Young Thug]] from his third studio album ''[[See You Next Wednesday (album)|See You Next Wednesday]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Belly Enlists The Weeknd, Young Thug For 'Better Believe' |url=https://915thebeat.com/news/8052089/belly-enlists-the-weeknd-young-thug-for-better-believe/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803203646/https://915thebeat.com/news/8052089/belly-enlists-the-weeknd-young-thug-for-better-believe/ |archive-date=August 3, 2021 |access-date=August 3, 2021 |website=91.5 The Beat |language=en}}</ref>

===2021–2023: ''Dawn FM''===
[[File:The Weeknd Portrait by Brian Ziff.jpg|thumb|The Weeknd in August 2021]]
On August 2, 2021, Tesfaye released a snippet of new music on social media.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9608939/the-weeknd-the-dawn-is-coming-new-music|title=The Weeknd Previews New Era With 'The Dawn Is Coming' Teaser: Watch|last=Lynch|first=Joe|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=August 2, 2021|access-date=August 2, 2021|archive-date=August 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802131336/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9608939/the-weeknd-the-dawn-is-coming-new-music/|url-status=live}}</ref> He appeared on the cover of the September 2021 issue of ''[[GQ]]'', marking the magazine's first global publication.<ref>{{Cite web|date=August 2, 2021|title=Announcing the Worldwide Era of GQ|url=https://www.gq.com/story/editors-letter-september-2021|access-date=August 2, 2021|website=GQ|language=en-US|archive-date=August 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802111546/https://www.gq.com/story/editors-letter-september-2021|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=August 2, 2021|title=The Weeknd vs. Abel Tesfaye|url=https://www.gq.com/story/the-weeknd-september-cover-interview|access-date=August 2, 2021|website=GQ|language=en-US|archive-date=March 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220301172754/https://www.gq.com/story/the-weeknd-september-cover-interview|url-status=live}}</ref> Then, in a collaboration with [[NBC Sports]] and the [[2020 Summer Olympics]], Tesfaye announced his single "[[Take My Breath]]", which was released on August 6.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hussey|first=Allison|date=August 2, 2021|title=The Weeknd Releasing New Song "Take My Breath" This Friday: Watch Preview|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-shares-preview-of-new-song-listen/|access-date=August 3, 2021|website=Pitchfork|language=en-US|archive-date=December 9, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211209102300/https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-shares-preview-of-new-song-listen/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Sinha|first=Charu|date=August 3, 2021|title=The Weeknd Announces New Single, 'Take My Breath'|url=https://www.vulture.com/2021/08/listen-the-weeknd-announces-new-single-take-my-breath.html|access-date=August 3, 2021|website=Vulture|language=en-us|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803050044/https://www.vulture.com/2021/08/listen-the-weeknd-announces-new-single-take-my-breath.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that month, he appeared on [[Kanye West]]'s tenth studio album ''[[Donda (album)|Donda]]'' on the track "[[Hurricane (Kanye West song)|Hurricane]]", which won [[Grammy Award for Best Melodic Rap Performance|Best Melodic Rap Performance]] at the [[64th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Every Song on Kanye West's 'Donda' Album, Ranked: Critic's Pick|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9611383/kanye-west-donda-album-songs-ranked|access-date=September 2, 2021|magazine=Billboard|date=August 29, 2021|language=en|archive-date=August 30, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210830002338/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9611383/kanye-west-donda-album-songs-ranked|url-status=live}}</ref>

On October 4, 2021, during an episode of ''Memento Mori'', Tesfaye revealed that his fifth studio album was complete and that he was waiting on a "couple characters that are key to the narrative."<ref>{{Cite magazine|first=Heran|last=Mamo|title=The Weeknd Says His Next Album Is 'Complete'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9640546/the-weeknd-new-album-complete/|date=October 5, 2021|access-date=October 5, 2021|magazine=Billboard|language=en|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161112/https://mb.moatads.com/n.js?e=35&ol=616457646&qn=%604%7BZEYwoqI%24%5BK%2BdLLU)%2CMm~tR%23e.%5BMhS%3A15.snxNz3%2B1bmlLntoDUj%7B!%3CFeid%5BOV%7C%2B2x%3D(%3Ce7%25%7DSlx%3Am4%2C..8WLdA1%3BxTiWio8bYLaXBjA%3AmQ)%3CF!tAbjrzJ%3BgoVYGVxc%40lQQV%23tc3%2Fh%7C%3FVKV%3BaBgS%3F%2BWx%3Ba5%2F%5BGI%3F4YtmN%3Dn%3Cy)j%3BG%24%7D%23%2F8YCC2J.bq!CASw%5EXm0okt%24b_o%3FtVD%5D%5BpN%7CQF%40Sy7%7B%2CNr1U*%26ujMUU8fvb%26%22B&tf=1_nMzjG---CSa7H-nHVQZC-bW7qhB-LRwqH-nMzjG-&vi=111111&rc=0%2C0%2C0%2C0%2C0%2C1%2C0%2C0%2Cprobably%2Cprobably&rb=1-u0LprlteFlxSeIKWBFuET31Epk3Oj90BFaPgx%2FCwrOl2tvnQIIWF3cA%2B&rs=1-VkX1JxJzs6uFgA%3D%3D&sc=1&os=1-kw%3D%3D&qp=00000&&iv=8&qt=0&gz=0&hh=0&hn=0&tw=%40Dmfv)6YAS&qc=0&qd=0&qf=1400&qe=900&qh=1400&qg=900&qm=0&qa=1400&qb=900&qi=1400&qj=900&to=000&po=1-0020002000002120&vy=ot%24b%5Bh%40%22oDgO%3DLlE6%3AYnIBMwqCf%5D)4%5Dz%2C%5B%26u9L%2F%2F%24b4%5DIAIbzbld%7Dt00%7Ca_BB%3FVxyEO%22zf4%5D%24cr16Zh5YigBghs%7ClTr1W*d%5B4kf%2FLyUoRdByZ%3C99Ks(I%7DY(T0c%7BDQ3MY.NjDby7p%26C&ql=&qo=0&qr=0&i=TRAVELAUDIENCE_DISPLAY1&hp=1&wf=1&ra=1&pxm=7&sgs=3&vb=7&kq=1&hq=0&hs=0&hu=0&hr=0&ht=0&dnt=0&bq=0&f=0&j=&t=1698595871669&de=682657930032&m=0&ar=0c7a73c5c3d-clean&iw=eaa0026&q=2&cb=0&ym=0&cu=1698595871669&ll=2&lm=0&ln=1&r=0&em=0&en=0&d=30000487%3A50005204%3A60023909%3A70014673&zMoatSSP=0&zMoatDeal=-1&zMoatSubdomain=billboard.com&zMoatIMPID=zvviOiY1MqIa1x_z2D58CsvyY5NtEk-ol_fF1w&zMoatGSR=1&ph=&pj=standard&zGSRC=1&gu=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.billboard.com%2Fmusic%2Fpop%2Fthe-weeknd-new-album-complete-9640546%2F&id=1&ii=4&bo=832aeb183ab3408baf361e325c1e760c.safeframe.googlesyndication.com&bd=300x250&zMoatOrigSlicer1=832aeb183ab3408baf361e325c1e760c.safeframe.googlesyndication.com&zMoatOrigSlicer2=300x250&zMoatDomain=billboard.com&gw=travel198849194933&fd=1&it=500&ti=0&ih=2&pe=1%3A1182%3A1182%3A0%3A1397&jk=-1&jm=-1&fs=205668&na=1883493068&cs=0&ord=1698595871669&jv=1043408664&callback=DOMlessLLDcallback_99927131|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 18, Tesfaye announced that his upcoming tour, originally titled the After Hours Tour, would be held entirely in stadiums due to arena constraints and was scheduled to commence in July 2022.<ref>{{Cite magazine|first=Daniel|last=Kreps|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-after-hours-til-dawn-north-american-stadium-tour-1315843/|title=The Weeknd Sets 'After Hours Til Dawn' North American Stadium Tour|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=March 3, 2022|access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303155331/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-after-hours-til-dawn-north-american-stadium-tour-1315843/|archive-date=March 3, 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> The tour was renamed as the [[After Hours til Dawn Tour]], and would incorporate elements from his fourth and fifth studio albums.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Aswad|first=Jem|date=October 18, 2021|title=The Weeknd Moves Tour Dates to Summer 2022|url=https://variety.com/2021/music/news/the-weeknd-after-hours-tour-dates-to-summer-2022-1235091675/|access-date=October 24, 2021|website=Variety|language=en-US|archive-date=October 18, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211018154928/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/the-weeknd-after-hours-tour-dates-to-summer-2022-1235091675/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=The Weeknd Announces 'After Hours Til Dawn' Stadium Tour|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2021/10/18/the-weeknd-after-hours-til-dawn-stadium-tour/|access-date=October 24, 2021|website=Rap-Up|language=en-US|archive-date=October 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211024153636/https://www.rap-up.com/2021/10/18/the-weeknd-after-hours-til-dawn-stadium-tour/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On October 22, 2021, Tesfaye appeared on [[Swedish House Mafia]]'s single "[[Moth to a Flame]]" from their debut studio album ''[[Paradise Again]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Aswad|first=Jem|date=October 22, 2021|title=The Weeknd and Swedish House Mafia Team Up for Smoldering New Single, 'Moth to a Flame'|url=https://variety.com/2021/music/news/weeknd-swedish-house-mafia-new-single-moth-to-a-flame-1235095476/|access-date=October 24, 2021|website=Variety|language=en-US|archive-date=October 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211024141826/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/weeknd-swedish-house-mafia-new-single-moth-to-a-flame-1235095476/|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 5, he appeared on [[Post Malone]]'s single "[[One Right Now]]" from his fourth studio album ''Twelve Carat Toothache''.<ref>{{Cite web|date=November 3, 2021|title=Listen to a snippet of Post Malone and The Weeknd's new collaboration 'One Right Now'|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/post-malone-the-weeknd-collaboration-one-right-now-3085963|access-date=November 4, 2021|website=NME|language=en-GB|archive-date=November 11, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111214321/https://www.nme.com/news/music/post-malone-the-weeknd-collaboration-one-right-now-3085963|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|title=The Weeknd & Post Malone Tease First-Ever Collaboration: Listen|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9654735/the-weeknd-post-malone-song-tease/|access-date=November 4, 2021|magazine=Billboard|date=November 3, 2021|language=en|archive-date=November 11, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111214345/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9654735/the-weeknd-post-malone-song-tease/|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 11, he was featured on [[Rosalía]]'s single "[[La Fama (song)|La Fama]]" from her third studio album ''[[Motomami]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Rosalía and the Weeknd share trailer for new track "La Fama"|url=https://www.thefader.com/2021/11/08/rosala-and-the-weeknd-share-trailer-for-new-track-la-fama|access-date=November 9, 2021|website=The FADER|language=en|archive-date=November 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211108232158/https://www.thefader.com/2021/11/08/rosala-and-the-weeknd-share-trailer-for-new-track-la-fama|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Sport|date=November 8, 2021|title=Rosalía - La Fama: Así es la primera canción del nuevo disco de Rosalía junto a 'The Weeknd'|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/cultura/fama-sera-primera-cancion-nuevo-12794023|access-date=November 9, 2021|website=sport|language=es|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161007/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/cultura/fama-sera-primera-cancion-nuevo-12794023|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 16, Tesfaye was featured on [[FKA Twigs]]' single "[[Tears in the Club]]" from her debut mixtape ''[[Caprisongs]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|date=December 13, 2021|title=FKA twigs teases new The Weeknd collaboration 'Tears In The Club'|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/fka-twigs-teases-new-the-weeknd-collaboration-tears-in-the-club-3117604|access-date=December 14, 2021|website=NME|language=en-GB|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161025/https://www.nme.com/news/music/fka-twigs-teases-new-the-weeknd-collaboration-tears-in-the-club-3117604|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Sisavat|first=Monica|date=December 14, 2021|title=FKA Twigs Teases a Collab With The Weeknd, and It Sounds Like a Total Banger|url=https://www.popsugar.com/node/48649449|access-date=December 14, 2021|website=POPSUGAR Entertainment|language=en-US|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029160626/https://www.instagram.com/p/CVLDiXlqZa1/embed/captioned/?cr=1&v=14&wp=658&rd=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popsugar.com&rp=%2Fbeauty%2Fhush-cut-49287201|url-status=live}}</ref> The next day, on December 17, he was featured on [[Aaliyah]]'s single "[[Poison (Aaliyah song)|Poison]]" from her posthumous album ''[[Unstoppable (Aaliyah album)|Unstoppable]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=December 14, 2021|title=The Weeknd Follows Drake & Chris Brown By Landing Posthumous Aaliyah Collaboration|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.66511/title.the-weeknd-follows-drake-chris-brown-by-landing-posthumous-aaliyah-collaboration|access-date=December 15, 2021|website=HipHopDX|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161008/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.66511/title.the-weeknd-follows-drake-chris-brown-by-landing-posthumous-aaliyah-collaboration|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=December 14, 2021|title=Aaliyah's Posthumous Song With The Weeknd "Poison" Coming Soon: Report|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/aaliyahs-posthumous-song-with-the-weeknd-poison-coming-soon-report-news.144584.html|access-date=December 15, 2021|website=HotNewHipHop|language=en|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161015/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/387689-aaliyahs-posthumous-song-with-the-weeknd-poison-coming-soon-report-news|url-status=live}}</ref>

Tesfaye released his fifth studio album ''[[Dawn FM]]'' on January 7, 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|first1=Nina|last1=Corcoran|first2=Jazz|last2=Monroe|date=January 3, 2022|title=The Weeknd Releasing New Album Dawn FM This Week|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-releasing-new-album-dawn-fm-this-week/|access-date=January 3, 2022|website=Pitchfork|language=en-US|archive-date=January 3, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220103142639/https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-releasing-new-album-dawn-fm-this-week/|url-status=live}}</ref> Upon release, the album debuted at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 with 148,000 units, marking Tesfaye's eighth top ten entry and his second non-consecutive album to debut at number two.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=January 18, 2022|title=Gunna Scores Second No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'DS4Ever'|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/gunna-tops-billboard-200-chart-ds4ever-1235019775/|access-date=January 19, 2022|magazine=Billboard|language=en-US|archive-date=January 18, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118172202/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/gunna-tops-billboard-200-chart-ds4ever-1235019775/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Gunna's 'DS4EVER' Scores the No. 1 Spot on the Billboard 200 as The Weeknd's 'Dawn FM' Debuts at No. 2|url=https://www.complex.com/music/gunna-ds4ever-first-week-sales|access-date=January 19, 2022|website=Complex|language=en|archive-date=January 18, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118223756/https://www.complex.com/music/gunna-ds4ever-first-week-sales|url-status=live}}</ref> He also broke the record for the most simultaneous entries for a male soloist on the [[Billboard Global 200|''Billboard'' Global 200]], with twenty-four songs on the chart.<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Weeknd Breaks Billboard Global 200 Record With 'Dawn FM'|url=https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-breaks-global-200-chart-record-with-dawn-fm|access-date=January 20, 2022|website=Complex|language=en|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161509/https://www.complex.com/music/a/cmplxjoshua-espinoza/the-weeknd-breaks-global-200-chart-record-with-dawn-fm|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Unterberger|first=Andrew|date=January 19, 2022|title=The Weeknd's New 'Dawn FM' Tops Charts Around The World, Showing His 'Undeniable Global Appeal'|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/the-weeknds-dawn-fm-top-charts-world-1235020035/|access-date=January 20, 2022|magazine=Billboard|language=en-US|archive-date=January 20, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120033009/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/the-weeknds-dawn-fm-top-charts-world-1235020035/|url-status=live}}</ref> In addition to "Take My Breath", ''Dawn FM'' was supported by the singles "[[Sacrifice (The Weeknd song)|Sacrifice]]" and "[[Out of Time (The Weeknd song)|Out of Time]]".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Watch The Weeknd's New Video for "Sacrifice" |url=https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-sacrifice-video |access-date=April 20, 2022 |website=Complex |language=en |archive-date=January 8, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108030952/https://www.complex.com/music/the-weeknd-sacrifice-video |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Daniela|last=Avila|url=https://people.com/music/the-weeknd-drops-out-of-time-music-video-featuring-jim-carrey/|title=The Weeknd Drops a Creepy, Karaoke-Singing 'Out of Time' Music Video — and It Features Jim Carrey!|website=People|date=April 5, 2022|access-date=April 19, 2022|language=en-US|archive-date=October 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161515/https://people.com/music/the-weeknd-drops-out-of-time-music-video-featuring-jim-carrey/|url-status=live}}</ref> February 26, Tesfaye premiered ''The Dawn FM Experience'', a television music special in partnership with [[Amazon Prime Video]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |date=February 21, 2022 |title=The Weeknd to Premiere 'Dawn FM Experience' Special This Weekend |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-dawn-fm-experience-special-prime-video-1310313/ |access-date=April 20, 2022 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=February 23, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230223165719/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-dawn-fm-experience-special-prime-video-1310313/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:The Weeknd Universal Studios Hollywood.jpg|left|thumb|The Weeknd's haunted house as part of [[Universal's Halloween Horror Nights]].]]
On March 20, the Weeknd played in an episode of the cartoon ''[[The Simpsons]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |date=March 21, 2022 |title=Watch The Weeknd appear in new episode of 'The Simpsons' |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-the-weeknd-appear-in-new-episode-of-the-simpsons-3186557 |access-date=April 22, 2023 |work=NME |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161517/https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-the-weeknd-appear-in-new-episode-of-the-simpsons-3186557 |url-status=live }}</ref> On April 18, he headlined the Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival for the second time, performing alongside Swedish House Mafia.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=April 18, 2022 |title=The Weeknd Closes Out Coachella With Hit-Filled, Tag-Team Set With Swedish House Mafia |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/the-weeknd-coachella-swedish-house-mafia-1235234529/ |access-date=April 20, 2022 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=October 29, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029161519/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/the-weeknd-coachella-swedish-house-mafia-1235234529/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=April 18, 2022 |title=Coachella 2022: The Weeknd covers Kanye, Drake as part of hits-filled headlining set |url=https://consequence.net/2022/04/coachella-2022-the-weeknd-kanye-drake-setlist/ |access-date=April 20, 2022 |website=Consequence |language=en-US |archive-date=April 20, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420032453/https://consequence.net/2022/04/coachella-2022-the-weeknd-kanye-drake-setlist/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On July 26, 2022, the Weeknd announced that he would host a [[Universal's Halloween Horror Nights#Haunted houses|haunted house]] at [[Universal Studios Florida]] and [[Universal Studios Hollywood|Hollywood]], as part of [[Universal's Halloween Horror Nights]] hosted every Halloween.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=July 26, 2022 |title=The Weeknd Brings 'After Hours' to Universal Studios' Halloween Horror Nights |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-after-hours-nightmare-halloween-horror-nights-1388229/ |access-date=August 26, 2022 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=August 26, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220826152429/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-after-hours-nightmare-halloween-horror-nights-1388229/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Tesfaye appeared on the song "[[Creepin' (Metro Boomin, the Weeknd and 21 Savage song)|Creepin']]" from Metro Boomin's album, ''[[Heroes & Villains]]'', on December 2, 2022.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Brodsky|first=Rachel|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2207303/stream-metro-boomins-new-album-heroes-villains-feat-the-weeknd-travis-scott-young-thug-more/music/|title=Stream Metro Boomin's New Album Heroes & Villains Feat. The Weeknd, Travis Scott, Young Thug, & More|magazine=Stereogum|date=December 2, 2022|access-date=April 6, 2024|archive-date=January 14, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114205921/https://www.stereogum.com/2207303/stream-metro-boomins-new-album-heroes-villains-feat-the-weeknd-travis-scott-young-thug-more/music/|url-status=live}}</ref> His song "[[Nothing Is Lost (You Give Me Strength)]]," made for the film [[Avatar: The Way of Water (soundtrack)|''Avatar: The Way of Water'']]{{'}}s official soundtrack, was released on December 16, 2022.

On February 24, 2023, following months-long renewed interest in and virality of the Weeknd's 2016 song "Die for You," which began charting in 2022 and reached a new peak of 6 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 6 years after its release, [[Die for You (The Weeknd song)|a remix]] of the song featuring Ariana Grande was released. The remix marked their fourth collaboration.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Strauss |first=Matthew |date=February 24, 2023 |title=The Weeknd Enlists Ariana Grande for New "Die for You (Remix)" |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-enlists-ariana-grande-for-new-die-for-you-remix-listen/ |access-date=February 27, 2023 |website=Pitchfork |language=en-US |archive-date=August 19, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819222159/https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-enlists-ariana-grande-for-new-die-for-you-remix-listen/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |date=February 6, 2023 |title=Miley Cyrus' 'Flowers' Tops Billboard Hot 100 for Third Week, Lil Uzi Vert's 'Just Wanna Rock' Hits Top 10 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/miley-cyrus-flowers-lil-uzi-vert-just-wanna-rock-hot-100-top-10-1235213867/ |access-date=February 27, 2023 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=February 7, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230207064022/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/miley-cyrus-flowers-lil-uzi-vert-just-wanna-rock-hot-100-top-10-1235213867/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 issue dated March 11, 2023, the remix reached the top of the chart, becoming both artists' seventh number one hit.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |date=March 6, 2023 |title=The Weeknd & Ariana Grande's 'Die for You' Leaps to No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/the-weeknd-ariana-grande-die-for-you-number-one-billboard-hot-100-1235280422/ |access-date=March 7, 2023 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=March 6, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230306180602/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/the-weeknd-ariana-grande-die-for-you-number-one-billboard-hot-100-1235280422/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On February 27, 2023, in the wake of the remix's success, the Weeknd became the first artist to surpass 100 million monthly listeners on Spotify.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Rowley |first=Glenn |date=February 27, 2023 |title=The Weeknd Becomes First Artist to Hit This Spotify Milestone |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-spotify-100-million-monthly-listeners-1235263328/ |access-date=February 28, 2023 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=February 28, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230228015429/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-spotify-100-million-monthly-listeners-1235263328/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On March 3, 2023, the Weeknd released his first live album, titled ''[[Live at SoFi Stadium]].''<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/the-weeknd-first-live-album-live-at-sofi-stadium-1235279121/|title=The Weeknd Drops First Live Album, 'Live at SoFi Stadium'|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|magazine=Billboard|date=March 3, 2023|accessdate=March 3, 2023|archive-date=March 10, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230310143734/https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/the-weeknd-first-live-album-live-at-sofi-stadium-1235279121/|url-status=live}}</ref> It featured recordings from his HBO concert film of the same name, showcasing the last concert of the North American leg of his [[After Hours til Dawn Tour]] at [[SoFi Stadium]]. He subsequently featured on four songs — "Artificial Intelligence," "Defame Moi," "More Coke!!," and "Emotionless" — from [[Mike Dean (record producer)|Mike Dean]]'s album ''[[4:23]]'', released on April 29, 2023. In May 2023, the Weeknd stated that he was intending to retire the moniker of "the Weeknd" in favor of performing under his birth name, or adopting a new pseudonym altogether. He explained that his upcoming album would most likely serve as his "final hurrah" under the name.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/the-weeknd-doesnt-want-to-be-the-weeknd-anymore |title=The Weeknd Doesn't Want to Be The Weeknd Anymore |last=Holmes |first=Helen |website=The Daily Beast |date=May 8, 2023 |publisher=The Daily Beast Company LLC |access-date=May 8, 2023 |archive-date=May 8, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230508200344/https://www.thedailybeast.com/the-weeknd-doesnt-want-to-be-the-weeknd-anymore |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== 2023–present: ''The Idol'' and ''Hurry Up Tomorrow'' ===
The Weeknd co-created the [[HBO]] drama series ''[[The Idol (TV series)|The Idol]]'' with [[Sam Levinson]], and stars in the show alongside [[Lily-Rose Depp]]. The series premiered at the [[2023 Cannes Film Festival]] out of competition, where it received significant controversy for its graphic depiction of onscreen nudity and sexual content. The series debuted to widespread negative reviews from critics. ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' stated that the series confirms the allegations that "Instead of subtly skewering the misogynistic and predatory nature of the business, ''The Idol'' became a forbidden love story — the stuff of a toxic man's fantasy", and called it "regressive rather than transgressive".<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-reviews/the-idol-review-lily-rose-depp-and-the-weeknd-in-an-hbo-series-thats-more-regressive-than-transgressive-1235497665/|title= 'The Idol' Review: Lily-Rose Depp and The Weeknd in an HBO Series That's More Regressive Than Transgressive|website= [[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date= May 23, 2023|accessdate= June 19, 2023|archive-date= May 23, 2023|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20230523014216/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-reviews/the-idol-review-lily-rose-depp-and-the-weeknd-in-an-hbo-series-thats-more-regressive-than-transgressive-1235497665/|url-status= live}}</ref> He received negative reviews for his acting, with critic Robert Daniels of ''The Playlist'' writing, "Tesfaye is also a terrible actor. He lacks the comfortability, the gravitas, charisma, and charm to increase the viability of Jocelyn being attracted to him. In most scenes, Tesfaye either hides under the cover of dim lighting, obtrusive coverage, or re-recorded dialogue dubbed into several scenes."<ref>{{cite web|url= https://theplaylist.net/the-idol-review-sam-levinsons-crude-provocation-with-the-weeknd-lily-rose-depp-is-gross-sexist-cannes-20230523/|title= 'The Idol' Review: Sam Levinson's Crude Provocation With The Weeknd & Lily-Rose Depp Is Gross & Sexist [Cannes]|website= The Playlist|date= May 23, 2023|accessdate= June 19, 2023|archive-date= June 19, 2023|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20230619064317/https://theplaylist.net/the-idol-review-sam-levinsons-crude-provocation-with-the-weeknd-lily-rose-depp-is-gross-sexist-cannes-20230523/|url-status= live}}</ref> On August 28, 2023, HBO announced it had cancelled ''The Idol'' after one season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Campione |first=Katie |date=August 28, 2023 |title='The Idol' Canceled At HBO After One Season |url=https://deadline.com/2023/08/the-idol-canceled-at-hbo-after-one-season-1235429399/ |access-date=August 29, 2023 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=August 29, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230829042346/https://deadline.com/2023/08/the-idol-canceled-at-hbo-after-one-season-1235429399/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On June 8, 2023, the Weeknd announced a series of [[Extended Play|EP]]s featuring [[Music from The Idol|music from ''The Idol'']]. Originally intended as a [[soundtrack album]], each EP was released following the premiere of each episode of the show, which featured collaborations with [[Future (rapper)|Future]], [[Playboi Carti]], [[Madonna]], [[Lil Baby]], [[Lily-Rose Depp]], and [[Jennie (singer)|Jennie]] from the South Korean girl group [[Blackpink]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Galindo |first1=Thomas |title=The Weeknd Announces Soundtrack for Upcoming HBO Series 'The Idol' |url=https://americansongwriter.com/the-weeknd-announces-soundtrack-for-upcoming-hbo-series-the-idol/ |website=American Songwriter |date=April 12, 2023 |access-date=June 12, 2023 |archive-date=May 18, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230518045900/https://americansongwriter.com/the-weeknd-announces-soundtrack-for-upcoming-hbo-series-the-idol/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Later in June he received an invitation from [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|the Academy]] to become a member.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |date=June 28, 2023 |title=Movie Academy Invites Nearly 400 New Members Including Taylor Swift, Ke Huy Quan, The Daniels & Austin Butler |url=https://deadline.com/2023/06/oscars-academy-membership-invites-2023-list-1235426384/ |access-date=June 28, 2023 |website=Deadline |archive-date=September 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230913115533/https://deadline.com/2023/06/oscars-academy-membership-invites-2023-list-1235426384/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On July 21, Tesfaye appeared on Travis Scott's lead single "[[K-pop (song)|K-pop]]" from his fourth studio album [[Utopia (Travis Scott album)|''Utopia'']],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Madarang |first=Charisma |date=July 21, 2023 |title=Travis Scott Releases 'K-POP,' Recruits The Weeknd and Bad Bunny |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/travis-scott-k-pop-the-weeknd-bad-bunny-song-1234792160/ |access-date=November 26, 2023 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=December 8, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208190115/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/travis-scott-k-pop-the-weeknd-bad-bunny-song-1234792160/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and later appeared on another track on Scott's album, "[[Circus Maximus (song)|Circus Maximus]]". Tesfaye appeared on [[Diddy (rapper)|Diddy]]'s single "[[Another One of Me]]" on September 15, which he called his "final feature",<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Blistein |first=Jon |date=September 15, 2023 |title=Diddy Busts Out 'In the Air Tonight' Sample for the Weeknd's Final Feature on 'Another One of Me' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/diddy-another-one-of-me-final-weeknd-feature-1234825947/ |access-date=November 26, 2023 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=December 8, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208190115/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/diddy-another-one-of-me-final-weeknd-feature-1234825947/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mamo |first=Heran |date=August 11, 2023 |title=The Weeknd Says He's Done With Features — Unless This Group Gets Back Together |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-final-feature-unless-daft-punk-reunites-1235390268/ |access-date=November 26, 2023 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=November 27, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231127001545/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-final-feature-unless-daft-punk-reunites-1235390268/ |url-status=live }}</ref> despite releasing multiple collaborations with [[Metro Boomin]] and [[Future (rapper)|Future]] in 2024.

On December 2, 2023, [[Fortnite]] announced that the Weeknd would be featured as the headlining artist for its [[Fortnite Festival]] gamemode and outfits of him would become available to play with on December 9. His outfits have three different variants of himself; the red suit seen throughout the promotional material for ''After Hours'', the outfit from his 2022 Coachella performance, and two of the costumes that he was seen wearing during the After Hours til Dawn Tour.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 9, 2023 |title=Fortnite Festival Season 1: Opening Night Features The Weeknd! |url=https://www.fortnite.com/news/fortnite-festival-season-1-opening-night-features-the-weeknd?lang=en-US |access-date=March 2, 2024 |language=en-US |archive-date=March 2, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240302195944/https://www.fortnite.com/news/fortnite-festival-season-1-opening-night-features-the-weeknd?lang=en-US |url-status=live }}</ref>

Tesfaye first teased news of a follow-up album to ''[[Dawn FM]]'' in 2022, telling his fans: "[I] wonder... did you know you're experiencing a new trilogy?" via [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=January 10, 2022 |title=The Weeknd: 'Did You Know You're Experiencing a New Trilogy?' |website=[[Complex Networks]] |url=https://www.complex.com/music/a/brad-callas/the-weeknd-did-you-know-youre-experiencing-a-new-trilogy |access-date=March 2, 2024 |language=en-US |archive-date=March 2, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240302200914/https://www.complex.com/music/a/brad-callas/the-weeknd-did-you-know-youre-experiencing-a-new-trilogy |url-status=live }}</ref> On January 8, 2024, he further teased an upcoming album, posting pictures of his last two albums and a question mark on his social media.<ref>{{Cite web |date=January 8, 2024 |title=3️⃣ |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/C10UBfGPQpj/ |access-date=March 2, 2024 |archive-date=January 22, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240122144012/https://www.instagram.com/p/C10UBfGPQpj/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On March 22, 2024, he appeared on the track "[[Young Metro]]" from Future and [[Metro Boomin]]'s collaborative album, ''[[We Don't Trust You]]'' as well as several tracks on Future and Metro Boomin's ''[[We Still Don't Trust You]]'' album.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Horvath|first=Zachary|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/779893-young-metro-music-video-future-metro-boomin-the-weeknd-hip-hop-news|title=Future, Metro Boomin, & The Weeknd Reunite Once Again For "Young Metro" Music Video|magazine=HotNewHipHop|date=March 25, 2024|access-date=April 7, 2024|archive-date=April 6, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240406155720/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/779893-young-metro-music-video-future-metro-boomin-the-weeknd-hip-hop-news|url-status=live}}</ref>

On July 17, 2024, Tesfaye announced a one-night show in São Paulo, Brazil, set to take place on September 7, 2024.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bloom|first=Madison|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-announces-one-night-only-stadium-concert-in-sao-paulo/|title=The Weeknd Announces One-Night Only Stadium Concert in São Paulo|website=Pitchfork|date=July 17, 2024|access-date=July 17, 2024}}</ref> He announced the title of his upcoming sixth album, ''[[Hurry Up Tomorrow]]'', three days prior to the concert.<ref>{{Cite x |number=1831324908510470596 |user=theweeknd |title=ALBUM TITLE |first=Abel |last=Tesfaye |date=September 4, 2024 |access-date=September 4, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=September 4, 2024 |title=The Weeknd Reveals Title, New Details About Next Album |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/the-weeknd-reveals-title-new-details-album-hurry-up-tomorrow-1236129931/ |access-date=September 4, 2024 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref>

